1
00:00:25,951 --> 00:00:28,954
SIX SINGLES UNDER ONE ROOF

2
00:00:29,655 --> 00:00:32,992
DAY 3, DINNER

3
00:00:33,058 --> 00:00:34,093
FULL OF ENDLESS MIRTH

4
00:00:34,159 --> 00:00:35,494
I'm exhausted.

5
00:00:35,561 --> 00:00:37,796
Let's have dinner out in the yard.

6
00:00:37,863 --> 00:00:39,999
Take the ingredients with you!

7
00:00:40,065 --> 00:00:42,167
- Sure thing.
- Yes, ma'am.

8
00:00:42,234 --> 00:00:43,969
FIRST-EVER BARBECUE PARTY TOGETHER

9
00:00:44,036 --> 00:00:47,973
EVERYONE HAS GOTTEN USED TO HAVING
6 CHAIRS AROUND THE TABLE AT MEALTIME

10
00:00:48,040 --> 00:00:49,108
Let me push this aside.

11
00:00:49,174 --> 00:00:50,776
- We can use it later.
- Good idea.

12
00:00:50,843 --> 00:00:52,344
It'd get in the way otherwise.

13
00:00:53,212 --> 00:00:57,716
ALPHA GIRL SOO-JIN WASTES NO TIME
IN SETTING UP THE GRILL

14
00:00:58,450 --> 00:00:59,618
It's cold.

15
00:01:00,085 --> 00:01:01,353
It's pretty chilly.

16
00:01:01,420 --> 00:01:02,421
SETS UP THE TABLE PEACEFULLY

17
00:01:02,655 --> 00:01:03,989
Shall I get it for you?

18
00:01:04,056 --> 00:01:05,224
TIDY DA-HEE NEVER SITS STILL

19
00:01:05,291 --> 00:01:06,325
SPRING IN HER STEP

20
00:01:09,995 --> 00:01:11,931
WHERE ARE THE OTHER HOUSEMATES?

21
00:01:11,997 --> 00:01:13,599
- It won't take long.
- There's our general.

22
00:01:13,933 --> 00:01:16,068
EXCLAIMS

23
00:01:16,135 --> 00:01:18,170
HYPE DUO

24
00:01:18,237 --> 00:01:20,940
HYUK AND DO-YEON SEEM TO BE
IN CHARGE OF LIFTING THE MOOD

25
00:01:21,006 --> 00:01:22,408
Why are you all lined up?

26
00:01:22,474 --> 00:01:23,809
I haven't done much.

27
00:01:24,343 --> 00:01:25,911
You can go take a seat.
I'm almost done.

28
00:01:25,978 --> 00:01:26,979
I love watching the flames.

29
00:01:27,413 --> 00:01:29,014
- Do you guys enjoy firegazing?
- Sure.

30
00:01:29,081 --> 00:01:30,215
I love it so much.

31
00:01:30,583 --> 00:01:32,751
I don't get the zoning out part.
Is it like daydreaming?

32
00:01:33,319 --> 00:01:34,486
ZONING OUT JUST FINE

33
00:01:34,553 --> 00:01:36,322
Yes, the heat's too high.

34
00:01:37,222 --> 00:01:39,959
- I love the crackling sound.
- Right?

35
00:01:40,559 --> 00:01:41,961
I'm digging this vibe.

36
00:01:42,027 --> 00:01:43,262
TOASTING MARSHMALLOWS FOR SNACK

37
00:01:43,329 --> 00:01:44,463
These smell amazing.

38
00:01:44,530 --> 00:01:45,965
So sweet. Once they're toasted...

39
00:01:46,599 --> 00:01:48,734
FOOD TASTER TAKES A BIG BITE

40
00:01:49,168 --> 00:01:50,269
How is it?

41
00:01:50,903 --> 00:01:52,671
- It's great.
- Once the outside has...

42
00:01:52,738 --> 00:01:54,206
You can just eat them now.

43
00:01:54,273 --> 00:01:55,908
I'd say yours are toasted nicely.

44
00:01:55,975 --> 00:01:57,376
NOW?

45
00:01:58,077 --> 00:01:59,678
What do I do?

46
00:01:59,745 --> 00:02:01,380
What do I do?

47
00:02:01,447 --> 00:02:03,549
Blow on them.

48
00:02:03,749 --> 00:02:05,284
OH, NO!

49
00:02:06,719 --> 00:02:08,420
ONE FELL

50
00:02:08,487 --> 00:02:09,688
No!

51
00:02:09,755 --> 00:02:10,789
HUFFS

52
00:02:10,856 --> 00:02:11,857
Hey!

53
00:02:11,924 --> 00:02:13,225
- No!
- Not on there.

54
00:02:13,292 --> 00:02:14,293
Emergency!

55
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,761
- No!
- Hurry!

56
00:02:17,029 --> 00:02:18,764
- Hey!
- No!

57
00:02:18,831 --> 00:02:20,432
- Not on there.
- Emergency!

58
00:02:20,499 --> 00:02:21,867
- Be careful.
- Daniel!

59
00:02:21,934 --> 00:02:23,102
- Is it okay?
- I've got it now.

60
00:02:23,836 --> 00:02:25,571
- Guys.
- What's this?

61
00:02:25,638 --> 00:02:27,006
- It's all good.
- We've got an accident!

62
00:02:27,072 --> 00:02:29,141
- Guys, what was that about?
- Are you hurt?

63
00:02:29,208 --> 00:02:30,843
- What happened, Do-yeon?
- It's okay.

64
00:02:30,909 --> 00:02:33,345
- Should we have used less kindling?
- Do you want to take some out?

65
00:02:33,412 --> 00:02:34,913
The sticks shouldn't form a cone.

66
00:02:34,980 --> 00:02:36,715
No, don't topple the cone.

67
00:02:36,782 --> 00:02:39,151
- It's not time for that yet.
- All right.

68
00:02:39,218 --> 00:02:41,553
- Hey, step aside.
- Watch out for the flying embers.

69
00:02:41,620 --> 00:02:43,422
- Let's use these tongs.
- Oh, sure.

70
00:02:43,489 --> 00:02:44,556
- Wait...
- With these...

71
00:02:44,623 --> 00:02:45,958
- There you go.
- Where will you put it?

72
00:02:46,025 --> 00:02:47,092
Take it to the side.

73
00:02:47,159 --> 00:02:48,360
- Yes, right there.
- I've got this.

74
00:02:48,427 --> 00:02:49,995
- Watch out for the flying embers.
- Be careful.

75
00:02:50,062 --> 00:02:51,163
You might catch fire.

76
00:02:51,230 --> 00:02:53,766
- I'll spread the sticks out.
- That's good.

77
00:02:53,832 --> 00:02:55,067
Great.

78
00:02:55,134 --> 00:02:56,335
AT PEACE AGAIN

79
00:02:56,969 --> 00:02:57,970
Watch out!

80
00:02:58,037 --> 00:02:59,972
- Maybe we added too many.
- Be careful.

81
00:03:00,039 --> 00:03:01,340
CHOI DANIEL, AGE 40
LOVES MARSHMALLOWS

82
00:03:01,407 --> 00:03:03,876
- Be careful.
- I could say the same to you.

83
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:07,346
- Be very careful.
- I can't believe you're eating.

84
00:03:07,413 --> 00:03:09,848
Can you pass me the tongs, Do-yeon?

85
00:03:09,915 --> 00:03:11,583
- We have too much kindling.
- Let's take some out.

86
00:03:11,650 --> 00:03:13,252
Or maybe all, if I can have my way.

87
00:03:13,819 --> 00:03:15,421
- All sorted now.
- Yes, is it good now?

88
00:03:15,487 --> 00:03:17,022
- Are you taking more out?
- No, we're good now.

89
00:03:17,089 --> 00:03:18,457
This seems okay now.

90
00:03:18,524 --> 00:03:19,558
Let's keep a small fire.

91
00:03:19,625 --> 00:03:20,859
Is it for your marshmallows?

92
00:03:20,926 --> 00:03:22,494
Yes, bear with me.

93
00:03:22,961 --> 00:03:25,297
- Go right ahead.
- I admire your laser-sharp focus.

94
00:03:26,532 --> 00:03:28,567
ONE MORE PERSON
WITH A LASER-SHARP FOCUS

95
00:03:28,634 --> 00:03:30,235
We've got a marshmallow creature.

96
00:03:30,302 --> 00:03:31,837
PICKING UP PIECES

97
00:03:32,571 --> 00:03:34,506
We could make Dubai chewy cookies
with these marshmallows.

98
00:03:34,573 --> 00:03:35,774
CLEANING UP THE DROPPED MARSHMALLOW

99
00:03:35,841 --> 00:03:36,842
This is good.

100
00:03:36,909 --> 00:03:38,343
- I told you.
- I'm eating that, Do-yeon.

101
00:03:38,410 --> 00:03:40,012
- This right here?
- Yes, it's pretty good.

102
00:03:40,612 --> 00:03:42,014
It fell on my container, after all.

103
00:03:44,149 --> 00:03:45,317
Is that good?

104
00:03:45,918 --> 00:03:47,820
- You can all rest now.
- Okay.

105
00:03:47,886 --> 00:03:50,322
Once charcoal is heated up...

106
00:03:50,389 --> 00:03:51,924
LEAVE THE BARBECUE
TO TRUSTY CAPTAIN KYUNG

107
00:03:53,025 --> 00:03:54,426
HERE WE GO

108
00:03:54,493 --> 00:03:56,195
ASSISTANT AHN-GEL

109
00:03:56,261 --> 00:03:58,130
- Do I throw in everything?
- Yes, everything.

110
00:03:58,197 --> 00:03:59,698
ADD PORK BELLY AND SAUSAGES
ON SOO-JIN'S CUE!

111
00:04:00,766 --> 00:04:04,236
KEY ASPECT IN GRILLING:
FIRE MANAGEMENT

112
00:04:05,871 --> 00:04:08,140
I hear you can roast anything
once you master pork belly.

113
00:04:08,340 --> 00:04:10,042
That's tricky, though.

114
00:04:10,109 --> 00:04:11,610
- Right?
- What with the oil dripping down.

115
00:04:12,211 --> 00:04:14,680
DRAWN BY THE ENTICING SMELL
FILLING UP THE YARD

116
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:16,782
Oh, wow.

117
00:04:16,849 --> 00:04:19,184
GUESTS GATHER

118
00:04:19,451 --> 00:04:21,987
NOW I COME TO THINK OF IT...

119
00:04:22,221 --> 00:04:24,189
You guys remember Keun-suk, right?

120
00:04:24,256 --> 00:04:26,391
I must leave for work.

121
00:04:26,458 --> 00:04:27,459
Right, Keun-suk.

122
00:04:27,526 --> 00:04:28,694
- He's missing.
- Oh, right.

123
00:04:28,761 --> 00:04:30,729
- Bet you forgot about him.
- Sorry, Keun-suk.

124
00:04:30,796 --> 00:04:33,766
Let's have a proper party
when he returns.

125
00:04:33,832 --> 00:04:34,967
It's cooked through, all right.

126
00:04:35,934 --> 00:04:38,003
- Let's eat up before they get cold.
- Okay, let's dig in.

127
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:40,205
- Let's eat, everyone.
- What a feast.

128
00:04:40,272 --> 00:04:42,074
Let's dig in.

129
00:04:43,475 --> 00:04:44,810
Enjoy, everyone.

130
00:04:44,877 --> 00:04:46,411
Here.

131
00:04:46,478 --> 00:04:48,113
HURRIEDLY TAKING A BIG BITE

132
00:04:48,180 --> 00:04:49,348
Dig in.

133
00:04:52,284 --> 00:04:53,285
It's insanely good.

134
00:04:54,019 --> 00:04:55,687
Ms. Kyung.

135
00:04:55,754 --> 00:04:58,090
- Thank you.
- Great job, Ms. Kyung.

136
00:04:58,690 --> 00:04:59,858
Man, this is good.

137
00:05:00,058 --> 00:05:02,861
You've handled everything
like nobody's business

138
00:05:02,928 --> 00:05:04,196
so we get to eat with no effort.

139
00:05:04,429 --> 00:05:06,532
But grilling meat isn't that easy.

140
00:05:06,598 --> 00:05:07,966
- It's a lot of work.
- Really?

141
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,601
I'm loving this, Captain.

142
00:05:10,102 --> 00:05:11,570
I can do this again.

143
00:05:11,637 --> 00:05:13,305
- Hit me up anytime.
- Thanks, I'll remember that.

144
00:05:13,372 --> 00:05:14,373
TRADING EXPERT SERVICES

145
00:05:14,439 --> 00:05:15,941
Daniel has another House Squad Goal.

146
00:05:16,008 --> 00:05:17,476
Slow dancing, was it?

147
00:05:17,543 --> 00:05:18,544
Yes.

148
00:05:18,610 --> 00:05:19,912
- Interesting.
- I'm curious, though.

149
00:05:19,978 --> 00:05:21,747
Why slow dancing of all things?

150
00:05:21,814 --> 00:05:22,981
Has it always been your dream?

151
00:05:23,048 --> 00:05:25,217
Back when I was young

152
00:05:25,284 --> 00:05:27,452
- I'd watch movies and find...
- Oh, I get it now.

153
00:05:27,519 --> 00:05:29,021
Especially in foreign movies

154
00:05:29,087 --> 00:05:33,125
the leads in a restaurant
would suddenly start dancing.

155
00:05:33,192 --> 00:05:35,093
What's the movie called
where people tango?

156
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:36,328
<i>- Scent of a Woman.</i>
<i>- Scent of a Woman.</i>

157
00:05:36,395 --> 00:05:38,130
- Is your fantasy
- Yes.

158
00:05:38,197 --> 00:05:39,932
- close to that scene in that movie?
- Exactly.

159
00:05:40,599 --> 00:05:43,936
LIKE THE LEGENDARY SCENE
FROM <i>SCENT OF A WOMAN</i>

160
00:05:44,203 --> 00:05:46,004
<i>- With someone at the piano...</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

161
00:05:46,071 --> 00:05:47,406
<i>In a restaurant with a piano</i>

162
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:48,607
<i>I'd be dressed in a suit</i>

163
00:05:48,674 --> 00:05:51,543
<i>and my partner would be in a dress,</i>
<i>nothing too fancy, you know.</i>

164
00:05:51,610 --> 00:05:54,580
<i>We would dance in a ballroom,</i>
<i>without caring about anyone else.</i>

165
00:05:54,646 --> 00:05:57,549
<i>As if a pin spot were following us.</i>

166
00:05:58,217 --> 00:06:01,220
That scene impressed me deeply
back when I was little.

167
00:06:01,286 --> 00:06:02,454
ROMANTIC SCENE HAS STAYED WITH HIM

168
00:06:02,654 --> 00:06:05,123
As much as I loved
that scene from the movie

169
00:06:05,190 --> 00:06:08,260
I still thought
that I could never do it.

170
00:06:08,327 --> 00:06:12,097
But it's something
I want to try with you guys.

171
00:06:16,535 --> 00:06:18,704
SLOW DANCING
LIKE IN <i>SCENT OF A WOMAN...</i>

172
00:06:18,770 --> 00:06:19,938
AVOIDS EYE CONTACT

173
00:06:20,005 --> 00:06:21,273
It sure is a romantic dream.

174
00:06:21,807 --> 00:06:24,176
ABOUT THE SLOW DANCE SCENE
IN <i>SCENT OF A WOMAN...</i>

175
00:06:24,243 --> 00:06:27,446
THE MALE LEAD DANCED WITH A WOMAN

176
00:06:28,247 --> 00:06:31,617
ONE OF US HAS TO HELP HIM OUT!

177
00:06:31,917 --> 00:06:33,619
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

178
00:06:33,685 --> 00:06:35,120
SUDDENLY PENSIVE LIKE THE OTHERS

179
00:06:35,187 --> 00:06:36,521
Honestly

180
00:06:37,089 --> 00:06:39,958
out of all the House Squad Goals
I've mentioned so far

181
00:06:40,025 --> 00:06:41,059
I want this one the most.

182
00:06:41,460 --> 00:06:42,961
- I get it.
- Is that so?

183
00:06:45,998 --> 00:06:49,167
Here's the thing, though.
You need to learn the dance.

184
00:06:49,234 --> 00:06:50,903
No, he can lead you.

185
00:06:51,403 --> 00:06:53,438
- Is that so?
- Do you want to try, Daniel?

186
00:06:53,505 --> 00:06:55,073
- Shall we, then?
- You can guide me.

187
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:57,509
- It will work.
- We'll prove it to you right away.

188
00:06:57,576 --> 00:06:58,710
You'll see.

189
00:06:58,777 --> 00:06:59,912
PEACEKEEPER AHN-GEL VOLUNTEERS

190
00:07:00,112 --> 00:07:01,847
- We'd be out dining, right?
- Okay.

191
00:07:01,914 --> 00:07:03,949
- We'll eat these mushrooms.
- Yes, all relaxed.

192
00:07:04,016 --> 00:07:06,385
- Think of us as other diners.
- We'd chat over the meal.

193
00:07:06,451 --> 00:07:08,186
"It's so nice to see you tonight.

194
00:07:08,253 --> 00:07:09,288
The food is wonderful.

195
00:07:09,354 --> 00:07:10,923
Isn't the mushroom to die for?"

196
00:07:10,989 --> 00:07:13,492
MALE LEAD

197
00:07:13,959 --> 00:07:15,193
We'd chat over the meal.

198
00:07:15,260 --> 00:07:16,395
FEMALE LEAD

199
00:07:16,895 --> 00:07:18,931
Are you going to the restroom?

200
00:07:19,364 --> 00:07:20,966
- What's the matter?
- Where are you going?

201
00:07:21,033 --> 00:07:22,167
ENTRANCED BY MUSIC

202
00:07:23,135 --> 00:07:27,973
THEY TURN TO LOOK AT EACH OTHER
WHILE STILL MUNCHING ON THEIR FOOD

203
00:07:32,311 --> 00:07:33,812
LIGHT TOUCH

204
00:07:35,514 --> 00:07:36,782
What's the matter with you?

205
00:07:36,848 --> 00:07:38,183
What the heck?

206
00:07:39,985 --> 00:07:43,055
- As if there were only two of us.
- Exactly.

207
00:07:43,121 --> 00:07:44,389
- We'd ignore everyone...
- Yeah.

208
00:07:44,456 --> 00:07:45,991
- With our eyes locked, right?
- Exactly.

209
00:07:47,693 --> 00:07:48,760
Here they go.

210
00:07:49,895 --> 00:07:51,763
THEY SAID YOU COULD MAKE IT WORK
WITH THE GUY LEADING...

211
00:07:51,830 --> 00:07:54,266
OUT OF SYNC

212
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:55,834
- Who's the girl, you or me?
- Beats me.

213
00:07:55,901 --> 00:07:57,903
- Same here.
- Just spin me around.

214
00:07:57,970 --> 00:07:59,304
- You sure?
- Yes.

215
00:07:59,771 --> 00:08:01,540
- The other direction.
- Help me out.

216
00:08:01,606 --> 00:08:03,175
Guys, you make such a cute couple.

217
00:08:03,241 --> 00:08:04,576
You look lovely, Jae-hyeon.

218
00:08:04,643 --> 00:08:06,078
IT'S ALL GOOD
AS LONG AS I'M OFF THE HOOK

219
00:08:07,179 --> 00:08:08,180
Now, spin.

220
00:08:09,247 --> 00:08:10,782
A PROPER SPIN THIS TIME?

221
00:08:10,849 --> 00:08:12,250
- My gosh.
- Guys!

222
00:08:13,785 --> 00:08:15,721
- Slower, okay?
- Okay.

223
00:08:15,787 --> 00:08:17,389
- My gosh.
- Guys!

224
00:08:17,856 --> 00:08:19,257
They might end up kissing.

225
00:08:19,891 --> 00:08:21,526
- Pretty neat, right?
- Honestly...

226
00:08:21,593 --> 00:08:22,828
- You look lovely.
- Yeah.

227
00:08:22,894 --> 00:08:24,029
This is the vibe we want.

228
00:08:24,096 --> 00:08:25,764
- You look good together.
- What do you think?

229
00:08:25,998 --> 00:08:27,299
This is what I want.

230
00:08:28,033 --> 00:08:30,669
Why don't we give it a go together?

231
00:08:30,736 --> 00:08:31,837
Like a rehearsal, you know.

232
00:08:32,371 --> 00:08:34,806
AVOIDING COMMITMENT

233
00:08:34,873 --> 00:08:37,042
LIKE IT'S A CONTEST

234
00:08:37,609 --> 00:08:39,311
- All I need is that vibe.
- Just the feel of it.

235
00:08:39,378 --> 00:08:41,380
SILENCE

236
00:08:41,913 --> 00:08:43,782
- Just to see the height difference.
- Yeah, just that.

237
00:08:44,282 --> 00:08:45,751
SILENCE

238
00:08:45,817 --> 00:08:47,719
You don't need to dance.
Let me just check that out.

239
00:08:47,786 --> 00:08:49,955
I'LL GIVE UP THE REST!
JUST STAND NEXT WITH ME...

240
00:08:50,255 --> 00:08:52,491
LOOKS AROUND

241
00:08:52,557 --> 00:08:56,161
DO-YEON RELUCTANTLY
STEPS UP FOR OLD TIME'S SAKE

242
00:08:57,429 --> 00:08:59,164
- I hope you're not badly upset.
- Why would I be?

243
00:08:59,231 --> 00:09:01,400
I've been waiting for this forever!

244
00:09:02,067 --> 00:09:04,870
I can barely contain my excitement!

245
00:09:05,837 --> 00:09:07,906
This is the best day of my life!

246
00:09:07,973 --> 00:09:09,007
SLOW-DANCE CRAZE

247
00:09:10,208 --> 00:09:11,209
All right, then.

248
00:09:11,276 --> 00:09:12,577
- Here's the deal.
- Hit me.

249
00:09:12,644 --> 00:09:14,246
- We'd share a meal together
- Okay.

250
00:09:14,312 --> 00:09:16,581
and recreate the scene
from start to finish.

251
00:09:16,648 --> 00:09:17,682
We'd be enjoying our meal

252
00:09:18,150 --> 00:09:19,851
<i>but we'd rise gracefully</i>
<i>when the music starts.</i>

253
00:09:21,386 --> 00:09:23,021
- Let's eat our meal.
- Okay.

254
00:09:23,088 --> 00:09:24,156
- Ignore the others.
- All right.

255
00:09:24,222 --> 00:09:25,657
- We're oblivious to them.
- Sure.

256
00:09:26,158 --> 00:09:27,292
This place is excellent.

257
00:09:27,359 --> 00:09:29,628
- Yeah, their steak is amazing.
- Tell me about it.

258
00:09:29,694 --> 00:09:31,663
- I see you're enjoying the steak.
- I love meat.

259
00:09:31,730 --> 00:09:33,265
- You're a meat lover?
- Yes.

260
00:09:34,599 --> 00:09:35,767
Do-yeon.

261
00:09:36,101 --> 00:09:37,102
Yes?

262
00:09:37,869 --> 00:09:39,371
Shall we dance?

263
00:09:39,805 --> 00:09:40,806
My gosh.

264
00:09:41,373 --> 00:09:42,441
Right now?

265
00:09:43,141 --> 00:09:45,343
- Are you sure? The place is packed.
- Don't worry. Let's go.

266
00:09:48,246 --> 00:09:49,514
The embarrassment might kill me.

267
00:09:49,581 --> 00:09:51,083
ERRATIC BEHAVIOR FROM EMBARRASSMENT

268
00:09:52,784 --> 00:09:54,419
I'm so embarrassed.

269
00:09:54,486 --> 00:09:55,787
- Don't worry.
- Can I dance like this?

270
00:09:56,221 --> 00:09:57,289
- It's okay.
- Like this?

271
00:09:57,355 --> 00:09:58,457
UTTERLY CHARMED

272
00:09:58,523 --> 00:10:00,325
- I'm really embarrassed.
- Don't worry about it.

273
00:10:00,392 --> 00:10:01,860
- It will be fine, Do-yeon.
- Okay.

274
00:10:01,927 --> 00:10:02,928
Do-yeon.

275
00:10:06,131 --> 00:10:08,333
SHYLY TAKES HIS HAND

276
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:09,534
- What do we do?
- Like this.

277
00:10:09,601 --> 00:10:12,170
- Do I just stare at you?
- We do this...

278
00:10:12,237 --> 00:10:14,106
At first, it goes like this.

279
00:10:14,739 --> 00:10:16,942
Who'd have thought?

280
00:10:17,709 --> 00:10:19,411
We maintain eye contact

281
00:10:19,478 --> 00:10:21,146
- and just shuffle this way and that.
- Okay.

282
00:10:21,580 --> 00:10:22,981
- Like this, okay?
- Sure.

283
00:10:23,849 --> 00:10:25,350
We sway like this.

284
00:10:25,417 --> 00:10:26,785
- Is this it?
- Yeah.

285
00:10:26,852 --> 00:10:29,387
- This is all I've imagined.
- I see.

286
00:10:29,621 --> 00:10:30,889
Let's move this way.

287
00:10:32,090 --> 00:10:33,225
Slowly...

288
00:10:34,926 --> 00:10:35,927
Slowly...

289
00:10:35,994 --> 00:10:38,697
FORCED TO RUN AWAY FROM EMBARRASSMENT

290
00:10:41,166 --> 00:10:43,101
DINNERTIME ON DAY 3

291
00:10:43,168 --> 00:10:44,903
THEY'VE EASED INTO SILLY PRANKS
AND SHARED LAUGHTER

292
00:10:44,970 --> 00:10:46,705
<i>What's changed from our first day?</i>

293
00:10:46,771 --> 00:10:47,806
We're relaxed.

294
00:10:48,607 --> 00:10:50,142
It's so easy to be around everyone.

295
00:10:50,542 --> 00:10:53,545
At first, we had to show the others
what we're like.

296
00:10:53,612 --> 00:10:56,915
Now, everyone has made that clear.

297
00:10:57,482 --> 00:10:58,817
SHARED MEALS

298
00:10:58,884 --> 00:11:00,785
SHARED DRINKS

299
00:11:00,852 --> 00:11:03,488
SHARED JOY

300
00:11:04,222 --> 00:11:08,393
NOW, THEY KNOW EVERYTHING
FROM EVERYONE'S LITTLE HABITS

301
00:11:08,460 --> 00:11:13,965
TO THE SECRETS
THEY'VE KEPT DEEP IN THEIR HEARTS

302
00:11:14,032 --> 00:11:16,234
If we lived together like this,
I'd have so much fun

303
00:11:16,301 --> 00:11:17,869
and never have a moment to feel down

304
00:11:17,936 --> 00:11:19,671
because the others
would always lend me their ear.

305
00:11:19,738 --> 00:11:21,673
But I wouldn't improve in any way.

306
00:11:24,109 --> 00:11:25,510
I'd never read a book.

307
00:11:26,645 --> 00:11:27,646
I can totally see it.

308
00:11:27,712 --> 00:11:28,713
IS IT OKAY TO JUST HAVE FUN?

309
00:11:29,114 --> 00:11:34,619
ANOTHER DAY WITH MIXED FEELINGS
AT GUGI-DONG COMES TO A CLOSE

310
00:11:35,053 --> 00:11:38,123
THE SUN RISES AGAIN ON DAY FOUR
WITH EVERYONE FEELING MORE AT EASE

311
00:11:38,557 --> 00:11:42,594
EARLY HOURS IN GUGI-DONG
ARE FILLED WITH QUICK MOVEMENTS

312
00:11:43,662 --> 00:11:46,331
GOOD MORNING

313
00:11:46,398 --> 00:11:51,069
EPISODE 4:
MY NEIGHBOR THE K-POP STAR

314
00:11:51,970 --> 00:11:56,841
NEXT-GENERATION MC IS UP ALONE
READING THE NEWSPAPER

315
00:11:56,908 --> 00:11:58,944
FOCUSED

316
00:12:00,478 --> 00:12:03,448
8 A.M.

317
00:12:04,115 --> 00:12:07,118
PEACEFUL MORNING

318
00:12:07,185 --> 00:12:11,089
DO-YEON BEGINS HER DAY
FOLLOWING HER MORNING ROUTINE

319
00:12:12,324 --> 00:12:14,426
LOOKING UP DIFFICULT EXPRESSIONS

320
00:12:14,492 --> 00:12:20,932
SHE'S EAGERLY EXPANDING
HER UNDERSTANDING OF CURRENT AFFAIRS

321
00:12:28,673 --> 00:12:30,642
WHAT'S THAT STRANGE SOUND
FROM NEXT DOOR?

322
00:12:30,976 --> 00:12:33,478
ARE MY EARS PLAYING TRICKS?

323
00:12:34,546 --> 00:12:37,515
IGNORES IT
AND RESUMES TO READING THE NEWSPAPER

324
00:12:38,116 --> 00:12:41,853
NEXT-GENERATION MC DOESN'T WAVER
IN HER MORNING STUDY HOUR

325
00:12:45,991 --> 00:12:48,693
AT THAT MOMENT,
THE NOISE TEASES HER EARS AGAIN

326
00:12:51,963 --> 00:12:53,031
BURSTS INTO LAUGHTER

327
00:12:53,098 --> 00:12:55,333
TURNS OUT DA-HEE IS SINGING
BEHIND THE WALL

328
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:56,568
What's she doing?

329
00:13:02,007 --> 00:13:05,710
QUIET AGAIN

330
00:13:06,878 --> 00:13:10,115
THE STRANGE VOICE
HAS GONE SILENT AGAIN

331
00:13:10,949 --> 00:13:13,485
MAYBE SHE WAS MUMBLING IN HER SLEEP

332
00:13:13,551 --> 00:13:16,621
LET'S GO BACK TO READING

333
00:13:20,825 --> 00:13:23,895
MYSTERIOUS NOISE
COMING FROM NEXT DOOR

334
00:13:24,396 --> 00:13:26,765
DECIDES TO EAVESDROP

335
00:13:28,133 --> 00:13:29,868
WHAT IS SHE DOING?

336
00:13:31,736 --> 00:13:35,740
DA-HEE IS SINGING <i>GOLDEN</i>
FROM <i>K-POP DEMON HUNTERS</i>

337
00:13:36,675 --> 00:13:39,411
THE NOISE CARRIES UNEXPECTEDLY WELL

338
00:13:39,477 --> 00:13:41,980
GRINS

339
00:13:43,248 --> 00:13:47,952
SINGING <i>GOLDEN </i>AT 8 A.M.

340
00:13:57,429 --> 00:13:59,798
VOICE CRACK HEARD LOUD AND CLEAR

341
00:14:00,498 --> 00:14:04,235
HOW IS IT THAT DA-HEE ENDED UP
SINGING QUITE LOUDLY?

342
00:14:04,302 --> 00:14:07,005
10 MINUTES AGO

343
00:14:07,605 --> 00:14:12,143
DA-HEE STARTED LOOKING FOR SOMETHING
RIGHT AFTER WAKING UP

344
00:14:17,615 --> 00:14:20,018
THE OBJECT SHE WAS LOOKING FOR...

345
00:14:20,085 --> 00:14:21,753
HER EARBUDS

346
00:14:22,153 --> 00:14:25,457
SHE WAS BEING MINDFUL
BEFORE HITTING THE PLAY BUTTON

347
00:14:26,558 --> 00:14:29,094
LITTLE DID DA-HEE REALIZE

348
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:31,996
THAT YOU TEND TO FORGET
HOW LOUD YOU'RE WHEN WEARING EARBUDS

349
00:14:33,665 --> 00:14:36,968
AND THAT THE WALLS
DIDN'T CANCEL NOISES AT ALL

350
00:14:37,402 --> 00:14:40,572
IT'S TIME DO-YEON TOLD HER THE TRUTH

351
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:43,508
SHOULD I GET OVER THERE OR NOT?

352
00:14:44,142 --> 00:14:46,745
SILENT

353
00:14:47,545 --> 00:14:49,414
She sure loves singing.

354
00:14:52,050 --> 00:14:53,618
SHOCKED

355
00:14:57,422 --> 00:14:59,724
IN THE MEANTIME

356
00:15:00,258 --> 00:15:01,926
KEUN-SUK RETURNED HOME
LATE AFTER WORK LAST NIGHT

357
00:15:01,993 --> 00:15:03,261
Me again?

358
00:15:04,396 --> 00:15:07,599
HE'S STILL THE FIRST PERSON
TO COME TO THE LIVING ROOM

359
00:15:08,533 --> 00:15:13,304
PRINCE NEVER SKIPS HIS BREAKFAST
NO MATTER HOW TIRED HE IS

360
00:15:14,272 --> 00:15:15,607
What?

361
00:15:15,673 --> 00:15:16,674
My gosh.

362
00:15:17,976 --> 00:15:19,577
WHY IS KEUN-SUK SO STARTLED?

363
00:15:19,644 --> 00:15:21,179
- Did you sleep well?
- Yeah.

364
00:15:21,246 --> 00:15:22,514
INSOMNIAC SOO-JIN APPEARED

365
00:15:22,881 --> 00:15:23,882
DEFYING EVERYONE'S EXPECTATIONS

366
00:15:23,948 --> 00:15:29,020
SOO-JIN HAD AN UNEXPECTED BEDTIME

367
00:15:29,254 --> 00:15:30,822
SHE SLEPT FOR 10 HOURS STRAIGHT

368
00:15:30,889 --> 00:15:33,158
AND APPEARED BARE-FACED
ON THEIR FIRST MORNING TOGETHER

369
00:15:33,224 --> 00:15:35,360
Well, she has insomnia.

370
00:15:35,427 --> 00:15:37,762
SHE SLEPT FOR 8 HOURS ON THE NEXT DAY

371
00:15:37,829 --> 00:15:42,000
HER SLEEPING SCHEDULE HAS SHOWN
A GREAT IMPROVEMENT IN GUGI-DONG

372
00:15:42,634 --> 00:15:44,068
TODAY...

373
00:15:44,135 --> 00:15:45,403
SHE APPEARED EARLY WITH MAKEUP ON

374
00:15:45,470 --> 00:15:47,272
- Did you sleep well?
- Yeah.

375
00:15:47,338 --> 00:15:49,174
I came home too late last night.

376
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:50,675
Really? And you're holding up okay?

377
00:15:50,742 --> 00:15:52,377
- Are you good?
- Sure.

378
00:15:52,811 --> 00:15:55,246
I see you never skip breakfast.

379
00:15:56,247 --> 00:15:57,449
Do you want some?

380
00:15:57,515 --> 00:15:59,017
I was thinking of making curry.

381
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,585
- Curry?
- Yes.

382
00:16:01,319 --> 00:16:02,587
In that case, I'll wait.

383
00:16:02,654 --> 00:16:04,088
I was thinking of making curry.

384
00:16:04,155 --> 00:16:05,590
- That sounds nice.
- Right?

385
00:16:06,224 --> 00:16:09,961
AFTER A GOOD NIGHT'S REST,
SOO-JIN HAD A LEISURELY MORNING

386
00:16:10,028 --> 00:16:11,930
GIVE ME BREAKFAST IDEAS
FOR OUR 6-MEMBER FAM

387
00:16:11,996 --> 00:16:13,531
SHE HAD A CHAT
WITH HER REGULAR AI FRIEND

388
00:16:14,532 --> 00:16:16,935
<i>I felt like making breakfast</i>
<i>for everybody.</i>

389
00:16:17,402 --> 00:16:20,205
<i>When I asked my AI chatbot for ideas,</i>
<i>it suggested making curry.</i>

390
00:16:21,039 --> 00:16:23,208
I have a name for my AI chatbot.

391
00:16:23,274 --> 00:16:24,342
I call it "My Rock."

392
00:16:26,711 --> 00:16:29,113
TAKE A SHOT OF THE INGREDIENTS
IN YOUR FRIDGE

393
00:16:29,180 --> 00:16:30,982
"WHAT CAN I ADD TO THE CURRY
AMONG THESE ITEMS?"

394
00:16:31,249 --> 00:16:33,952
THE CHATBOT WILL THEN TELL YOU
WHICH INGREDIENTS TO USE!

395
00:16:34,018 --> 00:16:35,653
LIST OF INGREDIENTS

396
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:37,422
SOO-JIN FOLLOWS
THE CHATBOT'S RECOMMENDATION

397
00:16:37,489 --> 00:16:39,290
FRESH INGREDIENTS:
ONION, CARROT, POTATO

398
00:16:39,357 --> 00:16:40,658
I'm adding canned corn.

399
00:16:40,725 --> 00:16:41,860
MUST-HAVES: CHILI, CORN, MEAT

400
00:16:42,694 --> 00:16:43,728
Great.

401
00:16:43,795 --> 00:16:45,797
THE INNOVATIVE YOUNGEST
IS COMMUNICATING WITH HER CHATBOT

402
00:16:46,030 --> 00:16:49,000
I noticed how so many people ask
their AI chatbots for recipes.

403
00:16:49,067 --> 00:16:50,168
I know.

404
00:16:50,235 --> 00:16:51,603
When I was teaching myself to cook

405
00:16:52,103 --> 00:16:53,404
we had to rely on YouTube.

406
00:16:54,839 --> 00:16:56,508
That was our best option.

407
00:16:57,842 --> 00:16:59,177
ANOTHER OLD-TIMER'S TIMELY ARRIVAL

408
00:16:59,244 --> 00:17:01,479
Why did you all get up so early?

409
00:17:01,546 --> 00:17:02,981
Morning, Daniel. Did you sleep well?

410
00:17:03,047 --> 00:17:06,551
- You're giving an unemployed uncle.
- What?

411
00:17:06,985 --> 00:17:08,086
Right?

412
00:17:09,354 --> 00:17:10,788
Seriously

413
00:17:10,855 --> 00:17:13,525
you look like a carefree uncle
who's given up on his career.

414
00:17:14,459 --> 00:17:16,494
You take so many supplements.

415
00:17:16,895 --> 00:17:19,664
NO SKIPPING THE DAILY ROUTINE

416
00:17:20,231 --> 00:17:22,300
You should take some, too.
Want to try these?

417
00:17:22,367 --> 00:17:24,235
- I can share them with you.
- What are they?

418
00:17:24,302 --> 00:17:25,470
No thanks.

419
00:17:25,770 --> 00:17:26,771
What's that, though?

420
00:17:26,838 --> 00:17:27,839
It's for men.

421
00:17:28,339 --> 00:17:31,743
FOR MEN?

422
00:17:31,809 --> 00:17:33,344
We should regularly take

423
00:17:33,411 --> 00:17:35,046
black maca, cumin

424
00:17:35,113 --> 00:17:37,148
something for our liver, omega-3...

425
00:17:37,215 --> 00:17:41,286
DANIEL IS BIG ON MEN'S HEALTH AS IS

426
00:17:41,586 --> 00:17:43,321
And probiotics.

427
00:17:43,388 --> 00:17:44,389
IN THAT CASE...

428
00:17:44,789 --> 00:17:46,724
Give me something
that isn't in pill form.

429
00:17:47,825 --> 00:17:49,160
Squeeze out every last drop.

430
00:17:49,227 --> 00:17:51,062
LET'S GO!

431
00:17:51,496 --> 00:17:53,164
What's all this early in the morning?

432
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:56,801
Let's go.

433
00:17:56,868 --> 00:17:59,637
MEN'S HEALTH SUPPLEMENT... IS BITTER

434
00:18:00,138 --> 00:18:02,006
CRACKS UP

435
00:18:02,073 --> 00:18:03,508
Olive oil makes it too greasy.

436
00:18:03,575 --> 00:18:05,243
I take lemon juice regularly.

437
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:07,445
Man, they're so energetic.

438
00:18:09,047 --> 00:18:11,149
ENERGETIC TUNE KEEPS FLOWING OUT
ON THIS SIDE OF THE HOUSE

439
00:18:11,215 --> 00:18:12,951
DO-YEON'S ROOM, DA-HEE'S ROOM

440
00:18:13,484 --> 00:18:16,387
BEDROOM KARAOKE IS STILL GOING WELL

441
00:18:18,923 --> 00:18:20,692
HUMMING ALONG

442
00:18:26,664 --> 00:18:28,866
VOICE CRACKING

443
00:18:30,201 --> 00:18:31,869
WHAT A BUMMER

444
00:18:34,772 --> 00:18:39,010
ASTOUNDED AT HERSELF
FOR FOCUSING MORE ON THE SONG

445
00:18:40,778 --> 00:18:44,916
NEXT-GENERATION SINGER
FINALLY SITS UPRIGHT

446
00:18:44,983 --> 00:18:46,217
CHANGES HER POSTURE

447
00:18:46,284 --> 00:18:47,885
PULLS IN HER CORE MUSCLES

448
00:18:48,386 --> 00:18:50,989
FULLY PREPARED TO BELT IT OUT

449
00:18:51,055 --> 00:18:52,590
8 A.M.
DA-HEE'S BEDROOM CONCERT

450
00:18:52,657 --> 00:18:54,225
SUNG BY DA-HEE, HEARD BY DO-YEON

451
00:18:59,764 --> 00:19:01,766
SHOWS INTEREST

452
00:19:09,507 --> 00:19:12,043
SURPRISED

453
00:19:12,477 --> 00:19:15,947
SOMEHOW ROOTING FOR DA-HEE
TO HIT THE HIGH NOTES

454
00:19:17,281 --> 00:19:20,718
GOES SILENT

455
00:19:21,152 --> 00:19:23,621
WHEN YOU FEEL UNSURE,
MAKE SURE TO SKIP THAT LINE

456
00:19:24,322 --> 00:19:27,492
HERE COMES THE IMPORTANT CHORUS PART!

457
00:19:35,033 --> 00:19:37,001
CRACKING UP

458
00:19:37,669 --> 00:19:41,305
LET'S GO
BEFORE DA-HEE WEARS HERSELF OUT

459
00:19:41,673 --> 00:19:42,940
Da-hee.

460
00:19:44,642 --> 00:19:45,910
Da-hee.

461
00:19:45,977 --> 00:19:46,978
Yes?

462
00:19:47,045 --> 00:19:48,212
Are you up?

463
00:19:48,279 --> 00:19:49,681
Yes, I am.

464
00:19:50,348 --> 00:19:52,450
WHAT'S GOING ON?

465
00:19:52,517 --> 00:19:55,453
What's with singing in the morning?

466
00:19:56,454 --> 00:19:57,622
What?

467
00:19:58,289 --> 00:20:00,591
Why are you belting out <i>Golden</i>
at this hour?

468
00:20:00,658 --> 00:20:01,859
- It's just...
- Tell me.

469
00:20:01,926 --> 00:20:03,494
What was that about with <i>Golden?</i>

470
00:20:03,561 --> 00:20:04,929
It's just that...

471
00:20:04,996 --> 00:20:08,633
I tried to keep it down
because I knew you were next door.

472
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:11,903
I wanted to sing that song so badly

473
00:20:11,969 --> 00:20:14,138
but I haven't memorized
the lines yet.

474
00:20:14,205 --> 00:20:15,606
I laughed my stomach out.

475
00:20:15,673 --> 00:20:17,508
It's so nice to be your roommate.

476
00:20:17,575 --> 00:20:18,676
FUN BEGINS EARLY IN THE MORNING

477
00:20:19,043 --> 00:20:20,078
Hi, guys.

478
00:20:20,144 --> 00:20:21,145
HOUSEMATES GATHERED TOGETHER

479
00:20:21,212 --> 00:20:22,346
Everyone's up.

480
00:20:22,947 --> 00:20:24,348
Good morning, Soo-jin.

481
00:20:24,682 --> 00:20:25,717
My gosh. Hey, Da-hee.

482
00:20:25,783 --> 00:20:26,918
JUST TWO DAYS AGO...

483
00:20:26,984 --> 00:20:30,755
DA-HEE WAS BUSY HIDING HER BARE FACE

484
00:20:31,089 --> 00:20:34,192
BUT ON DAY 4, SHE DOESN'T MIND AT ALL

485
00:20:34,258 --> 00:20:36,494
- Are you making breakfast?
- Yes, I'm making curry for you guys.

486
00:20:37,095 --> 00:20:39,497
My AI chatbot recommended curry.

487
00:20:39,964 --> 00:20:41,332
- You asked for its opinion?
- Yeah.

488
00:20:42,133 --> 00:20:43,901
The AI wants me to prepare curry.

489
00:20:43,968 --> 00:20:45,803
- Is Soo-jin making us curry?
- I mean

490
00:20:46,104 --> 00:20:47,338
you guys can take a breather.

491
00:20:47,839 --> 00:20:49,974
- I'll help out.
- You will? All right, then.

492
00:20:50,608 --> 00:20:52,577
JUST AN ASSISTANT AND NOT THE CHEF

493
00:20:52,643 --> 00:20:54,178
I'll do the dishes.

494
00:20:54,245 --> 00:20:55,980
- Use all the dishes you want.
- All right.

495
00:20:56,447 --> 00:20:58,750
We don't need to have everyone
working at the same time.

496
00:20:58,816 --> 00:20:59,984
THE 87ERS ARE ON BREAKFAST DUTY!

497
00:21:00,351 --> 00:21:02,153
DANIEL, THE 86ER,
IS STUCK IN THE MIDDLE

498
00:21:02,787 --> 00:21:04,589
- I'll take a rest.
- Can we really take a rest?

499
00:21:04,655 --> 00:21:06,090
Of course.

500
00:21:06,457 --> 00:21:09,694
THE 85ERS GET TO ENJOY THE FREE TIME
THANKS TO THE 87ERS AND "MY ROCK"

501
00:21:10,595 --> 00:21:12,797
MEANWHILE, DO-YEON HAS WASHED UP

502
00:21:13,464 --> 00:21:17,335
YOU CAN'T SKIP
THE MORNING SKINCARE ROUTINE

503
00:21:20,171 --> 00:21:21,939
DON'T FORGET TO MOISTURIZE YOUR HANDS

504
00:21:24,175 --> 00:21:25,777
I didn't get to finish my newspaper.

505
00:21:25,843 --> 00:21:27,278
PICKING UP WHERE SHE LEFT OFF

506
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:32,884
DA-HEE IS READING THE NEWSPAPER

507
00:21:33,618 --> 00:21:37,021
IT LOOKS LIKE SHE'S FOCUSING
PRETTY WELL THIS TIME

508
00:21:37,088 --> 00:21:38,222
OH, RIGHT

509
00:21:38,289 --> 00:21:39,423
Hey, Keun-suk.

510
00:21:40,291 --> 00:21:42,794
Do you like your room?

511
00:21:42,860 --> 00:21:43,861
OUT OF THE BLUE?

512
00:21:43,928 --> 00:21:45,062
It's not bad. Why do you ask?

513
00:21:45,129 --> 00:21:48,399
I hear Ms. Go suggested
we swap rooms for good luck.

514
00:21:48,933 --> 00:21:51,769
Let's ask about the room's colors.

515
00:21:51,836 --> 00:21:52,937
Does it suit us?

516
00:21:53,004 --> 00:21:54,539
Daniel in the Brown Room.

517
00:21:54,806 --> 00:21:56,474
Da-hee in the Yellow Room.

518
00:21:56,541 --> 00:21:57,809
I'd say Da-hee is the only person

519
00:21:57,875 --> 00:22:01,546
not fully in harmony with her color.

520
00:22:01,612 --> 00:22:04,315
Actually, it'd be better
if Keun-suk and Da-hee swapped rooms.

521
00:22:04,382 --> 00:22:06,450
KEUN-SUK IN THE YELLOW ROOM,
DA-HEE IN THE BLUE ROOM

522
00:22:06,517 --> 00:22:09,220
WITH ME?

523
00:22:09,687 --> 00:22:10,955
Do you like your room?

524
00:22:11,756 --> 00:22:13,357
Do you want to swap rooms?

525
00:22:13,424 --> 00:22:14,458
Not necessarily.

526
00:22:14,525 --> 00:22:17,228
- I like my room just fine.
- Da-hee.

527
00:22:17,295 --> 00:22:19,530
- There's one small problem.
- Which is?

528
00:22:19,597 --> 00:22:23,201
- Keun-suk and Do-yeon will...
- We'd have to share the bathroom.

529
00:22:25,303 --> 00:22:27,138
I don't think I can do that.

530
00:22:27,839 --> 00:22:29,507
I like yellow, you know.

531
00:22:29,841 --> 00:22:33,177
Can you give me something blue
from your room?

532
00:22:33,778 --> 00:22:35,780
- Like a talisman?
- Hey.

533
00:22:35,847 --> 00:22:37,315
- Give her your pajama.
- Do you want this?

534
00:22:37,381 --> 00:22:38,416
- Sure.
- Let her have it.

535
00:22:38,482 --> 00:22:40,718
- Wear this instead.
- Do you want to swap our pajamas?

536
00:22:40,785 --> 00:22:42,787
You know what?
Her nightshirt has red bits in it.

537
00:22:43,454 --> 00:22:44,455
<i>I told you.</i>

538
00:22:44,522 --> 00:22:46,390
<i>I don't trust such things blindly.</i>

539
00:22:46,958 --> 00:22:48,159
I'm not that kind of girl.

540
00:22:48,226 --> 00:22:50,561
Honestly, I don't care
about readings and stuff.

541
00:22:51,162 --> 00:22:52,997
Did you choose
blue slippers on purpose?

542
00:22:53,064 --> 00:22:55,066
- Good catch.
- No.

543
00:22:55,132 --> 00:22:57,301
<i>The shamans said</i>
<i>blue is the right color for me.</i>

544
00:22:57,368 --> 00:22:58,669
So...

545
00:22:58,736 --> 00:23:01,739
I'm trying to find the right balance
with some blue items in my life.

546
00:23:01,806 --> 00:23:03,174
Again, I'm not a blind follower.

547
00:23:03,241 --> 00:23:04,508
REPEATS HERSELF

548
00:23:04,575 --> 00:23:05,576
Be my guest.

549
00:23:05,643 --> 00:23:06,777
I'm not sure
if there's anything to take.

550
00:23:06,844 --> 00:23:07,912
- Do you want to check?
- Sure.

551
00:23:07,979 --> 00:23:08,980
RESPONSE IN 0.001 SECOND

552
00:23:10,114 --> 00:23:11,549
So you're into that kind of stuff.

553
00:23:11,616 --> 00:23:13,117
That's not it.

554
00:23:13,184 --> 00:23:14,552
Then why are you obsessing over it?

555
00:23:14,619 --> 00:23:16,354
I'm not obsessing over anything.
Here's the thing.

556
00:23:16,420 --> 00:23:18,322
The shamans said everyone was
in harmony with their color

557
00:23:18,389 --> 00:23:20,224
except for me.

558
00:23:20,291 --> 00:23:23,127
That really bugged me, you know.

559
00:23:23,494 --> 00:23:24,562
Something blue.

560
00:23:24,629 --> 00:23:25,630
How's the cushion?

561
00:23:26,297 --> 00:23:27,431
There's the stool, too.

562
00:23:28,432 --> 00:23:29,433
Flowers.

563
00:23:30,735 --> 00:23:33,237
The used cushion
is kind of icky, right?

564
00:23:33,304 --> 00:23:34,438
- No, not at all.
- Really?

565
00:23:34,505 --> 00:23:35,773
- It's okay.
- Turn it over.

566
00:23:35,840 --> 00:23:36,841
Yes, I like the idea.

567
00:23:36,908 --> 00:23:39,176
COLOR MATTERS MORE THAN CLEANLINESS

568
00:23:39,977 --> 00:23:42,213
- This is also blue.
- Can I take one of those

569
00:23:42,280 --> 00:23:43,881
and this blanket?

570
00:23:43,948 --> 00:23:45,149
I honestly don't mind.

571
00:23:45,216 --> 00:23:46,484
It's better than swapping rooms.

572
00:23:46,550 --> 00:23:47,618
Take whatever you want.

573
00:23:48,452 --> 00:23:49,754
- Okay.
- Take this, too.

574
00:23:49,820 --> 00:23:51,122
<i>Thanks, Keun-suk.</i>

575
00:23:51,188 --> 00:23:52,890
I MIND, SO I'LL GLADLY TAKE THESE

576
00:23:53,457 --> 00:23:55,059
SMILING

577
00:23:55,126 --> 00:23:56,294
- You seem almost giddy.
- Honestly

578
00:23:56,360 --> 00:23:59,163
the shaman's comment
really got under my skin.

579
00:23:59,230 --> 00:24:00,898
- With those in your room
- Yeah?

580
00:24:00,965 --> 00:24:02,233
you'll get a strong wealth fortune.

581
00:24:02,300 --> 00:24:04,435
You really think so? All right.

582
00:24:05,703 --> 00:24:08,205
AP'S WEALTH FORTUNE

583
00:24:08,272 --> 00:24:11,809
IS FILLING UP THE ROOM

584
00:24:12,443 --> 00:24:15,179
BELIEVE IT OR NOT

585
00:24:15,246 --> 00:24:17,648
DA-HEE IS NOT THE TYPE
TO BLINDLY FOLLOW SUPERSTITION

586
00:24:18,082 --> 00:24:20,017
SO MUCH WORK TO TACKLE

587
00:24:20,084 --> 00:24:21,652
I'll bring these
to your room, Keun-suk.

588
00:24:21,719 --> 00:24:23,487
I GUESS THERE'S NO STOPPING HER

589
00:24:23,554 --> 00:24:25,089
Are you giving me that blanket?

590
00:24:26,457 --> 00:24:27,692
Okay.

591
00:24:27,758 --> 00:24:29,560
DA-HEE HAS DISAPPEARED IN A FLASH

592
00:24:30,895 --> 00:24:33,364
RUSHING OVER TO KEUN-SUK'S ROOM
BEFORE HE CHANGES HIS MIND

593
00:24:34,065 --> 00:24:36,834
SHE KEPT SAYING SHE'S NOT A BELIEVER,
BUT HER SPEED SAYS OTHERWISE

594
00:24:37,501 --> 00:24:40,271
HURRIEDLY SETTING UP NEW ITEMS
DESPITE NOT BELIEVING THE SHAMANS

595
00:24:40,705 --> 00:24:44,442
MAKING MORE EFFORT
THAN IN HER OWN ROOM

596
00:24:44,508 --> 00:24:46,444
<i>It looked like a guy's room before.</i>

597
00:24:46,510 --> 00:24:48,245
<i>But with the new additions</i>

598
00:24:48,312 --> 00:24:50,748
<i>the room doesn't look</i>
<i>as cool as before.</i>

599
00:24:50,815 --> 00:24:52,249
That's the vibe I got

600
00:24:52,850 --> 00:24:54,552
so I felt kind of dumbfounded.

601
00:24:55,553 --> 00:24:59,924
NOW MOVING
AT A NOTICEABLY SLOWER PACE

602
00:25:00,624 --> 00:25:03,527
AGAIN, I DON'T BELIEVE IN SHAMANISM

603
00:25:03,761 --> 00:25:04,795
Let's go.

604
00:25:05,329 --> 00:25:06,931
- For a walk?
- I love the idea.

605
00:25:07,999 --> 00:25:09,400
Gosh, what a beautiful day it is.

606
00:25:09,467 --> 00:25:11,435
It's gotten much warmer, right?

607
00:25:12,303 --> 00:25:14,271
I haven't had a chance
to take a stroll around here.

608
00:25:14,338 --> 00:25:16,407
- Same. It's such a nice area.
- I know.

609
00:25:16,474 --> 00:25:17,842
OFF TO A CAFÉ NEARBY

610
00:25:18,075 --> 00:25:19,176
My gosh.

611
00:25:19,243 --> 00:25:21,579
There are so many hikers in the area.

612
00:25:22,380 --> 00:25:23,614
<i>Probably because it's the weekend.</i>

613
00:25:23,681 --> 00:25:26,217
<i>But it's lovely to go for a walk,</i>
<i>what with the warmer weather.</i>

614
00:25:26,751 --> 00:25:29,320
<i>- It's almost spring.</i>
<i>- Right?</i>

615
00:25:29,387 --> 00:25:31,822
<i>- It's great to go for a walk.</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

616
00:25:32,390 --> 00:25:35,426
THEY'VE BEEN STAYING IN GUGI-DONG
FOR 4 DAYS ALREADY

617
00:25:36,060 --> 00:25:37,495
Last night

618
00:25:37,561 --> 00:25:40,731
I dreamed of having
a flock of bats in my room.

619
00:25:40,798 --> 00:25:43,300
They even sat on my bed, you know.

620
00:25:43,367 --> 00:25:47,304
I tried to vacuum them and...

621
00:25:47,371 --> 00:25:49,173
You cleaned in your dream as well?

622
00:25:50,608 --> 00:25:52,209
- Did I clean?
- Gosh, Da-hee.

623
00:25:52,743 --> 00:25:54,578
- Well...
- You cleaned in your dream, too?

624
00:25:54,645 --> 00:25:56,347
I didn't clean, exactly.

625
00:25:56,414 --> 00:25:59,550
I only used a giant vacuum cleaner
to get rid of the bats...

626
00:25:59,617 --> 00:26:01,352
Most people would call that cleaning.

627
00:26:01,419 --> 00:26:03,020
- It was to capture them.
- You got them?

628
00:26:03,087 --> 00:26:04,288
- I did.
- You used the vacuum.

629
00:26:04,355 --> 00:26:05,823
They left dirt everywhere

630
00:26:05,890 --> 00:26:09,160
so I had to clean the dust
on my bed and other places.

631
00:26:09,226 --> 00:26:10,995
- Are you sure that was just a dream?
- I mean...

632
00:26:12,196 --> 00:26:13,197
So...

633
00:26:13,264 --> 00:26:15,099
It sounds like something
you'd do in real life.

634
00:26:15,166 --> 00:26:16,434
So I typed in details about my dream

635
00:26:16,500 --> 00:26:19,603
into an AI service
to get an interpretation.

636
00:26:19,670 --> 00:26:21,939
It said it was indicative
of high strain and stress.

637
00:26:23,507 --> 00:26:27,511
It said I was experiencing
mental pressure.

638
00:26:27,578 --> 00:26:29,580
I'm not lying here.
I really fed it to the chatbot.

639
00:26:29,847 --> 00:26:31,215
I know we've said

640
00:26:31,282 --> 00:26:33,884
that it's pretty enjoyable and fun,
but at the end of the day

641
00:26:33,951 --> 00:26:36,020
we moved into a new place, right?

642
00:26:36,787 --> 00:26:38,055
I don't know why for certain

643
00:26:38,122 --> 00:26:39,723
but I've come down with something.

644
00:26:42,059 --> 00:26:43,060
Honestly

645
00:26:43,127 --> 00:26:44,762
I'm actually enjoying it here

646
00:26:44,829 --> 00:26:46,497
but my body's reacting so strangely.

647
00:26:46,564 --> 00:26:47,832
I want to ask what's up with it.

648
00:26:47,898 --> 00:26:49,733
So you've been feeling that way, too.

649
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:51,836
You feel me? I want to tell my body,
"You enjoyed it, too."

650
00:26:52,036 --> 00:26:54,805
- We're adjusting to the new place.
- I think so.

651
00:26:54,872 --> 00:26:58,075
As much as I'm enjoying it,
my body can't help but tense up.

652
00:26:58,342 --> 00:27:01,579
I've kept thinking
that it's so easy to be here, too.

653
00:27:02,313 --> 00:27:04,415
But apparently,
my body doesn't agree.

654
00:27:04,482 --> 00:27:05,983
It must be under a lot of strain.

655
00:27:06,851 --> 00:27:09,019
- Here's the café.
- We got here in no time.

656
00:27:11,388 --> 00:27:13,257
- Hello.
- Hello.

657
00:27:13,324 --> 00:27:15,059
- Welcome.
- It's nice.

658
00:27:15,126 --> 00:27:18,496
- This is awesome. Hello.
- We should get some scones.

659
00:27:20,331 --> 00:27:21,732
My goodness.

660
00:27:21,799 --> 00:27:23,467
PLANNING TO COME BY OFTEN

661
00:27:23,767 --> 00:27:25,336
Will you be having the desserts here?

662
00:27:25,402 --> 00:27:27,104
No, they're for to go.

663
00:27:27,171 --> 00:27:28,239
Please pack them up.

664
00:27:28,305 --> 00:27:31,342
- I'll bring your order to you.
- Thank you.

665
00:27:33,811 --> 00:27:34,812
My gosh.

666
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:38,349
SPOTTED THE SIGNED CD CASES

667
00:27:38,415 --> 00:27:39,884
- Chung Kyung-hwa.
- Chung Kyung-hwa.

668
00:27:40,985 --> 00:27:42,953
CHUNG KYUNG-WHA
LEGENDARY KOREAN VIOLINIST

669
00:27:43,020 --> 00:27:45,289
- Did Chung Kyung-wha visit here?
- Yes.

670
00:27:46,090 --> 00:27:47,458
She lives on this side of the hill.

671
00:27:47,525 --> 00:27:49,293
- Really?
- Yes.

672
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:50,561
SHE'S IN OUR NEIGHBORHOOD?

673
00:27:50,628 --> 00:27:52,796
- It's incredible.
- She might've moved away

674
00:27:52,863 --> 00:27:54,698
but she signed our CDs
when she came by.

675
00:27:54,765 --> 00:27:56,333
That's incredible.

676
00:27:57,134 --> 00:27:58,469
<i>So this is a really nice area.</i>

677
00:27:58,536 --> 00:27:59,537
HOPE WE RUN INTO HER

678
00:27:59,937 --> 00:28:01,572
- Are they here?
- No, they're gone.

679
00:28:01,639 --> 00:28:02,773
All clear.

680
00:28:02,840 --> 00:28:04,875
MEANWHILE, TROUBLE SEEMS
TO BE BREWING IN THE HOUSE

681
00:28:04,942 --> 00:28:07,478
- You sure about going in?
- Can we just barge in like this?

682
00:28:08,479 --> 00:28:10,481
- Is anyone there?
- There's no one here.

683
00:28:11,549 --> 00:28:13,484
- Are they here?
- No, they're gone. All clear.

684
00:28:13,551 --> 00:28:16,153
- You sure about going in?
- Can we just barge in like this?

685
00:28:16,954 --> 00:28:18,255
Is anyone there?

686
00:28:18,322 --> 00:28:19,723
What a nice room.

687
00:28:19,790 --> 00:28:21,292
CUBBY LODGER IS JEALOUS

688
00:28:21,358 --> 00:28:22,960
This is Da-hee's...
No, it's Do-yeon's room.

689
00:28:23,561 --> 00:28:25,095
CLICK

690
00:28:26,363 --> 00:28:29,800
HE'S TAKING PHOTOS OUT OF THE BLUE

691
00:28:30,534 --> 00:28:32,636
Take a shot of this spot, Keun-suk.

692
00:28:32,703 --> 00:28:35,172
- Here?
- Let's say it went under the bed.

693
00:28:35,239 --> 00:28:36,240
COOKING UP A DETAILED SCHEME

694
00:28:36,574 --> 00:28:42,379
WHAT KIND OF PLOT
IS THIS TRIO HATCHING?

695
00:28:42,446 --> 00:28:44,281
RIGHT THEN!

696
00:28:44,348 --> 00:28:47,251
SOO-JIN COMES OUT TO THE LIVING ROOM

697
00:28:47,318 --> 00:28:48,419
That's the wrong switch.

698
00:28:48,652 --> 00:28:49,920
Three shots should be enough, right?

699
00:28:50,387 --> 00:28:53,324
- There is a gap...
- Someone's coming.

700
00:28:53,390 --> 00:28:56,860
IF THEY CATCH US, WE'RE SCREWED! RUN!

701
00:28:58,729 --> 00:29:01,565
THE TRIO RUNS INTO SOO-JIN IN THE END

702
00:29:01,932 --> 00:29:04,401
IS THIS IT FOR THEM?

703
00:29:04,468 --> 00:29:05,936
- We did it.
- My heart is racing.

704
00:29:06,003 --> 00:29:07,404
- It's perfect.
- You guys pulled it off?

705
00:29:07,471 --> 00:29:09,506
- Yes, we have so many photos.
- Really? Let's see them.

706
00:29:09,573 --> 00:29:11,842
- We can say it went under her bed.
- That's a good shot.

707
00:29:11,909 --> 00:29:14,511
Or we can have it sit on her chair.

708
00:29:14,578 --> 00:29:16,013
WHAT'S GOING ON?

709
00:29:16,280 --> 00:29:17,948
- Can we try something?
- What?

710
00:29:18,849 --> 00:29:19,950
You know

711
00:29:20,017 --> 00:29:23,187
the prank using photos
edited by AI chatbots.

712
00:29:23,254 --> 00:29:25,222
- I've seen the viral videos.
- Did you?

713
00:29:25,289 --> 00:29:26,857
- The AI prank.
- It's fascinating.

714
00:29:26,924 --> 00:29:27,958
- They're fun.
- So...

715
00:29:28,025 --> 00:29:30,294
<i>- Check your message.</i>
<i>- What's the matter?</i>

716
00:29:30,361 --> 00:29:33,063
<i>They came into our place.</i>

717
00:29:33,130 --> 00:29:35,266
<i>- They came into our place?</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

718
00:29:35,332 --> 00:29:38,535
<i>How could you put them on my bed?</i>

719
00:29:38,602 --> 00:29:40,237
<i>I didn't put them there.</i>

720
00:29:40,304 --> 00:29:41,972
<i>Don't tell me they pooped in my room.</i>

721
00:29:42,039 --> 00:29:43,040
LAUGHING ON MUTE

722
00:29:43,107 --> 00:29:44,675
We could say that pigeons came in

723
00:29:44,742 --> 00:29:46,410
and surprise them.

724
00:29:46,477 --> 00:29:49,013
Da-hee will likely fall for it.

725
00:29:49,079 --> 00:29:52,116
Let's plan it step-by-step.

726
00:29:52,182 --> 00:29:53,617
- The prompt matters the most.
- Got it.

727
00:29:53,684 --> 00:29:54,985
Give it detailed instructions.

728
00:29:55,052 --> 00:29:56,120
Let's say...

729
00:29:56,654 --> 00:30:00,257
Add a nest of pigeons

730
00:30:00,924 --> 00:30:03,961
- To the photo.
- into the photo.

731
00:30:05,729 --> 00:30:07,331
- Feed it this prompt.
- Let's do this.

732
00:30:08,399 --> 00:30:10,367
- It's generating image.
- Generating image.

733
00:30:10,434 --> 00:30:12,236
OLDIES AMAZED BY THE NEW TECH

734
00:30:12,670 --> 00:30:15,339
- I'll make another sample.
- Go ahead.

735
00:30:15,406 --> 00:30:18,676
We can make a bunch
since only we get to see them.

736
00:30:20,177 --> 00:30:22,346
