- We've got to do it like that.

859
00:34:29,660 --> 00:34:31,995
Guys, we're all set.
We don't need to send more photos.

860
00:34:32,062 --> 00:34:34,231
- It's time we called them.
- Yes, let's do that.

861
00:34:34,298 --> 00:34:35,699
Da-hee's old-school,
so she'll like calls.

862
00:34:35,766 --> 00:34:37,768
Let's keep our distance.

863
00:34:37,834 --> 00:34:39,937
- Right, our voices should echo.
- We're gathered too close.

864
00:34:40,003 --> 00:34:42,005
- Okay, I'm calling her now.
- Do it.

865
00:34:42,973 --> 00:34:44,408
I'll be over here.

866
00:34:44,808 --> 00:34:45,809
I'm going to run.

867
00:34:45,876 --> 00:34:48,812
ON STANDBY SLIGHTLY APART
JUST AS THEY PLANNED

868
00:34:52,382 --> 00:34:54,318
- Hey, it's coming down!
- Not just yet.

869
00:34:54,384 --> 00:34:55,385
- Get it!
- Hold on.

870
00:34:55,452 --> 00:34:58,021
ALREADY IN CHARACTER
EVEN BEFORE DA-HEE PICKS UP

871
00:34:58,088 --> 00:34:59,156
Hang on.

872
00:34:59,222 --> 00:35:00,490
Just a second.

873
00:35:00,557 --> 00:35:02,059
TOTALLY DEDICATED

874
00:35:02,125 --> 00:35:03,627
- She hasn't picked up yet?
- Not yet.

875
00:35:03,694 --> 00:35:06,263
DA-HEE ISN'T ANSWERING

876
00:35:06,330 --> 00:35:07,764
Should I call Do-yeon instead?

877
00:35:08,231 --> 00:35:10,400
- We could call her.
- I'll give it a go.

878
00:35:11,234 --> 00:35:13,770
After all this hard work,
we'll need a nap.

879
00:35:14,538 --> 00:35:16,039
SHE ANSWERED!

880
00:35:16,106 --> 00:35:17,741
- No, wait!
- Get it!

881
00:35:19,142 --> 00:35:20,410
SHE ANSWERED!

882
00:35:20,477 --> 00:35:22,212
- No, wait!
- Get it!

883
00:35:22,279 --> 00:35:23,680
We'll need a nap.

884
00:35:25,949 --> 00:35:28,318
STARTLED INTO SPITTING OUT THE GRAPE

885
00:35:28,385 --> 00:35:30,387
AWAY IT GOES

886
00:35:30,454 --> 00:35:32,122
WILD COMMOTION

887
00:35:32,189 --> 00:35:34,358
You guys haven't caught
the pigeon yet?

888
00:35:35,325 --> 00:35:37,160
<i>I'm sorry, but just a second.</i>

889
00:35:37,227 --> 00:35:38,996
- You really haven't had luck yet?
<i>- Wait!</i>

890
00:35:39,062 --> 00:35:40,430
- What's going on?
<i>- Excuse me.</i>

891
00:35:40,497 --> 00:35:41,632
Is it because of the pigeon?

892
00:35:41,698 --> 00:35:43,667
<i>- Can you stand aside?</i>
- Is everything all right?

893
00:35:43,934 --> 00:35:44,935
- What do we do?
- Should we go back?

894
00:35:45,002 --> 00:35:46,103
- Yeah.
<i>- I'll get it.</i>

895
00:35:47,104 --> 00:35:49,473
- Hello? Do-yeon!
- Back there!

896
00:35:49,539 --> 00:35:53,777
WHAT'S WITH ALL THIS BODY LANGUAGE?
THEY'RE NOT ON A VIDEO CALL

897
00:35:53,844 --> 00:35:56,246
Do-yeon, it's going crazy here.
I don't know what to do.

898
00:35:56,313 --> 00:35:57,314
Step aside, please.

899
00:35:58,148 --> 00:35:59,583
What's the matter?
Is it still in the house?

900
00:35:59,650 --> 00:36:00,751
<i>It's too big.</i>

901
00:36:00,817 --> 00:36:02,119
- It's too big?
<i>- You have no idea.</i>

902
00:36:03,420 --> 00:36:04,888
Hang on. I can't even...

903
00:36:04,955 --> 00:36:06,556
It's going to fly. Open the door!

904
00:36:06,623 --> 00:36:08,492
Open the door, for goodness' sake.

905
00:36:08,558 --> 00:36:10,394
21-YEAR VETERAN ACTOR'S
PIGEON PERFORMANCE

906
00:36:11,361 --> 00:36:12,696
What do we do?

907
00:36:12,763 --> 00:36:14,231
We'll be there to help.

908
00:36:14,297 --> 00:36:15,432
HASTILY PREPARING TO LEAVE

909
00:36:15,499 --> 00:36:17,300
- It's a mess.
- Wait, this is an actual emergency.

910
00:36:17,367 --> 00:36:18,368
Just a second.

911
00:36:18,435 --> 00:36:20,971
- Could you please...
- Do you need them in a to-go cup?

912
00:36:21,038 --> 00:36:22,572
Do you think you can catch a pigeon?

913
00:36:22,639 --> 00:36:24,741
I've never tried it.
Have you caught one before?

914
00:36:25,042 --> 00:36:26,309
