915
00:36:27,244 --> 00:36:29,179
- You must be talking about seagulls.
- Am I?

916
00:36:31,481 --> 00:36:33,417
GET IT TOGETHER

917
00:36:33,483 --> 00:36:34,785
Seagulls?

918
00:36:35,218 --> 00:36:36,486
I guess they look similar.

919
00:36:37,220 --> 00:36:39,089
- They're all birds, after all.
- That's true.

920
00:36:39,356 --> 00:36:40,757
- Here are your drinks.
- All right.

921
00:36:40,824 --> 00:36:42,259
- Thank you.
- Please come again.

922
00:36:42,325 --> 00:36:43,393
Thank you.

923
00:36:43,460 --> 00:36:44,961
MINDING THEIR MANNERS
EVEN IN A KEYED-UP STATE

924
00:36:45,028 --> 00:36:46,963
- Are they struggling to catch it?
- It seems like it.

925
00:36:47,030 --> 00:36:48,098
What do we do?

926
00:36:49,700 --> 00:36:52,703
ACTORS WITH 76 YEARS OF EXPERIENCE
ARE STILL COMMITTED TO THE BIT

927
00:36:52,769 --> 00:36:54,705
- It's time you got it, guys!
- She hung up.

928
00:36:54,771 --> 00:36:55,772
- What did she say?
- So?

929
00:36:56,073 --> 00:36:58,008
She asked us to get it
and then hung up.

930
00:36:58,075 --> 00:37:00,077
She sensed we couldn't really talk,
so she hung up.

931
00:37:00,143 --> 00:37:03,246
We were just doing our parts here.
You didn't have to join us.

932
00:37:03,313 --> 00:37:06,349
- Listen, I was out here.
- You could've stayed outside.

933
00:37:06,550 --> 00:37:08,685
- I talked to them from here.
- What did you say?

934
00:37:08,752 --> 00:37:09,953
- Tell us.
- "It went into your room.

935
00:37:10,020 --> 00:37:11,588
It's so huge."

936
00:37:11,655 --> 00:37:12,789
Who hung up first?

937
00:37:12,856 --> 00:37:15,258
What if they're pranking us somehow?

938
00:37:15,325 --> 00:37:16,326
Do-yeon hung up, okay?

939
00:37:16,393 --> 00:37:17,861
I didn't do it.

940
00:37:17,928 --> 00:37:18,962
She reacted and hung up.

941
00:37:19,029 --> 00:37:21,164
- You could've led them on...
- Exactly.

942
00:37:21,231 --> 00:37:23,366
You had to let us know
what was going on in the call.

943
00:37:23,433 --> 00:37:25,535
We could've settled down gradually

944
00:37:25,602 --> 00:37:27,471
- and then listened in.
- Should I call one more time?

945
00:37:28,538 --> 00:37:30,907
Let's tell them
it pooped on its way out.

946
00:37:32,042 --> 00:37:33,110
It left, but not before pooping.

947
00:37:33,376 --> 00:37:35,045
- Why don't you call her?
- I'll do it.

948
00:37:35,112 --> 00:37:36,246
PASSING THE BURDEN TO SOO-JIN

949
00:37:38,448 --> 00:37:42,552
GETTING INTO CHARACTER

950
00:37:43,487 --> 00:37:46,256
I feel like I need a nap.

951
00:37:46,723 --> 00:37:47,891
- I'm exhausted.
- Da-hee.

952
00:37:49,059 --> 00:37:50,060
Hey, Soo-jin.

953
00:37:50,427 --> 00:37:51,661
<i>- Da-hee.</i>
- What's up?

954
00:37:52,229 --> 00:37:53,630
<i>- Where are you?</i>
- What?

955
00:37:53,697 --> 00:37:55,699
We're on our way home.

956
00:37:56,133 --> 00:37:58,969
It's crazy, Da-hee.
We had such a big drama here.

957
00:37:59,035 --> 00:38:01,004
A big drama because of the pigeon?

958
00:38:01,071 --> 00:38:02,405
Yes, you know what?

959
00:38:02,472 --> 00:38:04,708
It pooped in your room.

960
00:38:04,775 --> 00:38:06,510
<i>It pooped in your room.</i>

961
00:38:07,844 --> 00:38:09,813
- Don't lie to me.
- What's wrong?

962
00:38:10,213 --> 00:38:11,214
Just...

963
00:38:11,281 --> 00:38:12,382
<i>Get a photo, guys.</i>

964
00:38:12,449 --> 00:38:13,984
- Hey...
<i>- Come on, hurry.</i>

965
00:38:14,384 --> 00:38:15,585
- What's wrong?
- Can you run, Do-yeon?

966
00:38:15,652 --> 00:38:16,653
What happened?

967
00:38:16,720 --> 00:38:17,854
- Darn it.
- What's this about?

968
00:38:17,921 --> 00:38:19,389
Are you serious?

969
00:38:19,456 --> 00:38:21,091
It pooped in my room!

970
00:38:21,158 --> 00:38:22,425
- Oh, no.
- I'm losing my mind.

971
00:38:22,492 --> 00:38:23,560
How tactless.

972
00:38:23,627 --> 00:38:25,228
It should have gone in my room.

973
00:38:26,196 --> 00:38:27,464
Oh, you poor thing.

974
00:38:27,531 --> 00:38:29,533
Give us a bit more time.
We're actually running home.

975
00:38:29,866 --> 00:38:31,134
We'll be right there.

976
00:38:31,735 --> 00:38:33,837
- I'll switch my room with you.
- Do-yeon.

977
00:38:33,904 --> 00:38:35,739
What a dumb bird, right?

978
00:38:35,806 --> 00:38:37,107
TEARFULLY BEAUTIFUL FRIENDSHIP

979
00:38:37,474 --> 00:38:38,542
I mean...

980
00:38:38,608 --> 00:38:40,744
HURRYING HOME AT THE SHOCKING NEWS

981
00:38:40,811 --> 00:38:41,812
I mean, just...

982
00:38:41,878 --> 00:38:43,246
They must be nearby.

983
00:38:43,313 --> 00:38:44,314
DING-DONG

984
00:38:46,950 --> 00:38:48,451
Guys, go hide in there.

985
00:38:48,518 --> 00:38:49,986
Remember my dream?

986
00:38:50,053 --> 00:38:52,522
About that dream with the bats.

987
00:38:53,323 --> 00:38:54,925
Maybe I should just go back home.

988
00:38:55,692 --> 00:38:57,627
No, it will be fine.

989
00:38:58,128 --> 00:39:00,297
I didn't realize
the café was so far away.

990
00:39:01,064 --> 00:39:02,065
We're here now.

991
00:39:04,835 --> 00:39:06,336
- Guys.
- Did you catch it?

992
00:39:06,403 --> 00:39:07,637
Well, we did.

993
00:39:07,704 --> 00:39:09,306
- You got it?
- But your rooms are a mess.

994
00:39:09,573 --> 00:39:11,842
Check if they look all right.
Go on, Da-hee.

995
00:39:12,342 --> 00:39:13,543
Well, mine looks...

996
00:39:14,244 --> 00:39:15,512
It looks fine to me.

997
00:39:15,579 --> 00:39:16,980
DO-YEON RELAXES

998
00:39:17,447 --> 00:39:19,049
5 SECONDS BEFORE THEY LEARN THE TRUTH

999
00:39:19,115 --> 00:39:23,320
4, 3, 2, 1...

1000
00:39:27,057 --> 00:39:28,124
Was it a prank?

1001
00:39:28,191 --> 00:39:29,626
- So it didn't poop in your room?
- Guys.

1002
00:39:29,693 --> 00:39:31,628
- You should of...
- Da-hee almost cried.

1003
00:39:31,695 --> 00:39:33,930
MIMICKING A PIGEON

1004
00:39:34,497 --> 00:39:37,267
PIGEON KEUN-SUK JUMPS OUT
FROM HIS HIDING PLACE

1005
00:39:38,435 --> 00:39:40,003
- What on earth?
- Seriously...

1006
00:39:40,070 --> 00:39:41,771
- See? He got the job done.
- Where's the pigeon?

1007
00:39:42,005 --> 00:39:43,506
This is what I'm talking about!

1008
00:39:44,407 --> 00:39:45,742
What was that pigeon in the photo?

1009
00:39:46,443 --> 00:39:47,677
It was an AI-generated photo.

1010
00:39:47,744 --> 00:39:50,580
- Was it fake?
- They used the AI for that!

1011
00:39:50,647 --> 00:39:52,649
- Seriously?
- The AI chatbot made it for us.

1012
00:39:53,250 --> 00:39:54,251
Chilling, right?

1013
00:39:54,317 --> 00:39:55,418
- Are you okay?
- Did you fall for it?

1014
00:39:55,485 --> 00:39:56,486
Neat, right?

1015
00:39:56,553 --> 00:39:57,754
RELIEVED TO FIND IT WAS A PRANK

1016
00:39:57,821 --> 00:40:00,724
- Guys, Da-hee almost cried.
- For real?

1017
00:40:00,790 --> 00:40:02,092
After hearing about the poop...

1018
00:40:02,158 --> 00:40:04,494
- She was this close to wailing.
- I considered leaving.

1019
00:40:04,561 --> 00:40:07,030
<i>I wondered, "Could this room</i>
<i>be cursed for me or what?"</i>

1020
00:40:07,097 --> 00:40:08,531
<i>Then, Soo-jin said</i>
<i>the bird even pooped.</i>

1021
00:40:08,732 --> 00:40:10,333
I had to draw a line at that.

1022
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:13,203
I considered leaving this place.

1023
00:40:13,603 --> 00:40:14,704
I mean it.

1024
00:40:15,405 --> 00:40:17,007
I would've cried
if it had actually happened.

1025
00:40:17,073 --> 00:40:18,141
Seriously.

1026
00:40:18,875 --> 00:40:21,244
Pull a stunt like this again
and I'll freaking kill you guys.

1027
00:40:21,311 --> 00:40:23,346
SUCCESSFUL AI PRANK ENDS
WITH A CHILLING WARNING

1028
00:40:23,413 --> 00:40:24,981
She said she'd kill us
if we tried this again.

1029
00:40:25,215 --> 00:40:26,783
We missed you that badly, that's all.

1030
00:40:26,850 --> 00:40:29,286
Didn't I tell you
we shouldn't try it, Soo-jin?

1031
00:40:29,352 --> 00:40:31,688
- You had fun, too.
- Gosh, that looks so good.

1032
00:40:31,755 --> 00:40:33,723
- She looks anxious.
- You're the worst.

1033
00:40:33,790 --> 00:40:35,225
ANOTHER HAPPY DAY WITH THE FAM

1034
00:40:35,292 --> 00:40:36,693
Wait, so should I serve rice now?

1035
00:40:37,260 --> 00:40:38,495
Yes, please.

1036
00:40:38,561 --> 00:40:39,863
CURRY IS ALSO READY

1037
00:40:39,930 --> 00:40:41,898
Hey, it looks delicious.

1038
00:40:41,965 --> 00:40:44,467
It looks special with the corn.

1039
00:40:45,602 --> 00:40:47,237
It kind of reminds me of soup.

1040
00:40:47,304 --> 00:40:49,339
- The witch's soup, right?
- Yeah.

1041
00:40:49,406 --> 00:40:50,907
I like that it's not too creamy.

1042
00:40:50,974 --> 00:40:51,975
Thank you.

1043
00:40:52,042 --> 00:40:54,077
- Everything's ready.
- We're all set.

1044
00:40:54,644 --> 00:40:56,846
<i>- Who fried the eggs?</i>
<i>- Soo-jin.</i>

1045
00:40:56,913 --> 00:40:59,249
<i>- Soo-jin prepared everything.</i>
<i>- Really?</i>

1046
00:40:59,316 --> 00:41:01,084
<i>- Kimchi looks amazing.</i>
<i>- Right?</i>

1047
00:41:01,151 --> 00:41:02,385
<i>Curry and kimchi are a winning combo.</i>

1048
00:41:02,452 --> 00:41:03,520
PERFECT PAIRING

1049
00:41:03,586 --> 00:41:04,955
- Bon appétit.
- Bon appétit.

1050
00:41:05,021 --> 00:41:06,356
Please enjoy.

1051
00:41:06,423 --> 00:41:07,824
I should take a picture.

1052
00:41:07,891 --> 00:41:09,159
Everything looks so pretty.

1053
00:41:09,225 --> 00:41:12,028
VISUALLY, IT'S AMAZING!
BUT WHAT ABOUT THE TASTE?

1054
00:41:13,096 --> 00:41:14,798
So? Is it good?

1055
00:41:14,864 --> 00:41:16,633
- It goes down smoothly, right?
- It's so good.

1056
00:41:16,700 --> 00:41:19,402
- I love it.
- I love the subtle spicy kick.

1057
00:41:19,469 --> 00:41:21,037
DELICIOUS

1058
00:41:21,104 --> 00:41:22,172
Ma'am.

1059
00:41:22,238 --> 00:41:23,873
- It's so good.
- It's decent, right?

1060
00:41:23,940 --> 00:41:25,008
Yes.

1061
00:41:25,075 --> 00:41:26,910
- The corns are killers.
- Agreed.

1062
00:41:27,477 --> 00:41:29,312
- That reminds me.
- Oh, wow.

1063
00:41:29,379 --> 00:41:31,247
Da-hee might have
a dance lesson later.

1064
00:41:31,314 --> 00:41:32,582
A dance lesson?

1065
00:41:32,782 --> 00:41:34,184
- Yes.
- What kind of a dance?

1066
00:41:34,250 --> 00:41:37,887
I mentioned that I would like
to take dance lessons with you guys

1067
00:41:37,954 --> 00:41:41,257
and shoot a dance challenge video.

1068
00:41:41,324 --> 00:41:42,759
Yes, I remember that.

1069
00:41:43,126 --> 00:41:44,627
There are so many genres, though.

1070
00:41:45,195 --> 00:41:47,530
There's this one dance
I'd like to learn.

1071
00:41:48,498 --> 00:41:49,632
The dance for <i>like JENNIE.</i>

1072
00:41:51,201 --> 00:41:53,403
A SONG BY JENNIE, OF ALL PEOPLE?

1073
00:41:53,470 --> 00:41:55,805
I couldn't learn the moves
from watching videos alone.

1074
00:41:55,872 --> 00:41:56,873
You need a tutor?

1075
00:41:56,940 --> 00:41:59,809
I feel like I could do it
if a tutor gave me pointers.

1076
00:42:00,176 --> 00:42:01,711
What did you learn
when you took lessons?

1077
00:42:02,178 --> 00:42:04,381
I learned the dance for Hwasa's song

1078
00:42:04,447 --> 00:42:07,017
<i>Maria, </i>for a dance challenge.

1079
00:42:08,752 --> 00:42:12,355
6 YEARS AGO, DA-HEE SHARED THIS VIDEO
ON HER SOCIAL MEDIA ACCOUNT

1080
00:42:12,422 --> 00:42:15,925
A PROMISING DANCER WANNABE
SOURCE: LEE DA-HEE HERSELF

1081
00:42:18,061 --> 00:42:20,730
STILL SO PASSIONATE

1082
00:42:21,331 --> 00:42:23,066
SHE MEANS BUSINESS

1083
00:42:23,133 --> 00:42:24,401
It's just...

1084
00:42:24,467 --> 00:42:26,636
With good pointers...

1085
00:42:26,703 --> 00:42:28,705
- You need a good tutor.
- Yes.

1086
00:42:28,772 --> 00:42:30,507
I want to learn from good tutors.

1087
00:42:30,573 --> 00:42:31,641
All right, then.

1088
00:42:32,142 --> 00:42:33,343
Let me see what I can do.

1089
00:42:33,576 --> 00:42:34,744
What have you got?

1090
00:42:35,345 --> 00:42:36,579
Are you familiar with Nika?

1091
00:42:36,646 --> 00:42:37,914
Who is this?

1092
00:42:38,181 --> 00:42:39,849
As in the dancer Monika.

1093
00:42:41,618 --> 00:42:42,886
From <i>Street Woman Fighter?</i>

1094
00:42:42,952 --> 00:42:44,354
Are you talking about Ms. Monika?

1095
00:42:44,788 --> 00:42:46,289
I'm friends with her.

1096
00:42:46,723 --> 00:42:49,192
You're close enough
to call her by a nickname?

1097
00:42:49,259 --> 00:42:51,428
We talk casually.

1098
00:42:51,494 --> 00:42:55,298
We appeared on the same shows
and even had meals together.

1099
00:42:55,365 --> 00:42:57,233
- I'm a huge fan.
- I'll ask if she's free.

1100
00:42:57,300 --> 00:43:01,571
Nika did mention that she'd have
some free time in February.

1101
00:43:02,372 --> 00:43:04,140
Were you able to get her on board?

1102
00:43:04,340 --> 00:43:05,341
Sure.

1103
00:43:05,775 --> 00:43:07,110
- She's really available?
- Yeah.

1104
00:43:07,177 --> 00:43:08,244
EXCITED

1105
00:43:08,311 --> 00:43:09,312
It's incredible.

1106
00:43:09,379 --> 00:43:11,347
UPSIDE OF HAVING HOUSEMATES
THEIR FRIENDS CAN BE MY FRIENDS

1107
00:43:11,414 --> 00:43:12,515
What's the genre, though?

1108
00:43:13,817 --> 00:43:14,984
Sports dancing?

1109
00:43:15,318 --> 00:43:17,187
- Sports dancing with this?
- What sports dance is this?

1110
00:43:17,253 --> 00:43:18,354
Well...

1111
00:43:18,721 --> 00:43:19,722
Something like jitterbug?

1112
00:43:19,789 --> 00:43:20,890
They do this for jitterbug?

1113
00:43:23,626 --> 00:43:26,696
They must be learning slow dancing
as a birthday gift for you.

1114
00:43:27,063 --> 00:43:28,264
No way.

1115
00:43:28,331 --> 00:43:29,332
- Seriously?
- Really?

1116
00:43:30,266 --> 00:43:31,534
That's what you're learning?

1117
00:43:31,801 --> 00:43:34,137
- Something trendy.
- Like hip-hop?

1118
00:43:34,504 --> 00:43:36,005
- Hip-hop?
- So hip-hop?

1119
00:43:36,239 --> 00:43:37,740
You don't need lessons for that.

1120
00:43:37,807 --> 00:43:39,676
- It's all about the groove.
- I know that

1121
00:43:39,742 --> 00:43:41,311
but I can't groove on my own

1122
00:43:41,377 --> 00:43:43,379
so I'm going to ask Ms. Monika to...

1123
00:43:43,580 --> 00:43:45,315
- Teach you how to free-style?
- Yes, a bit.

1124
00:43:45,381 --> 00:43:46,950
Ms. Monika?

1125
00:43:47,016 --> 00:43:48,318
I bet Do-yeon is great with hip-hop.

1126
00:43:48,384 --> 00:43:49,586
Let me come with you.

1127
00:43:49,652 --> 00:43:51,221
You saw my passion
for dancing, right?

1128
00:43:51,287 --> 00:43:52,522
TRYING TO WIN HER OVER

1129
00:43:52,589 --> 00:43:53,623
Oh, right.

1130
00:43:53,690 --> 00:43:55,391
OOPS, I FORGOT

1131
00:43:55,458 --> 00:43:58,228
I should show off
my one-kicks and two-kicks.

1132
00:43:59,395 --> 00:44:01,564
- They suit you. I bet you'd slay.
- I haven't heard them in ages.

1133
00:44:01,631 --> 00:44:03,233
The secret about those moves

1134
00:44:03,299 --> 00:44:04,901
is that tall people
can't do them so well.

1135
00:44:04,968 --> 00:44:06,202
What are they, anyway?

1136
00:44:06,870 --> 00:44:08,004
Have you never heard of them?

1137
00:44:08,071 --> 00:44:09,072
What are they?

1138
00:44:09,139 --> 00:44:10,640
Have you not read
the comic series <i>Hip-Hop?</i>

1139
00:44:11,274 --> 00:44:12,742
- No.
- Chills.

1140
00:44:12,809 --> 00:44:14,711
- You know it, right?
- I've read it a million times.

1141
00:44:14,777 --> 00:44:16,646
The first three moves we see
are one-kick, two-kick

1142
00:44:16,713 --> 00:44:18,248
- and a handstand called "Nikes."
- Show them.

1143
00:44:18,448 --> 00:44:20,483
Can't we get
a demonstration, Soo-jin?

1144
00:44:20,550 --> 00:44:22,352
- Show them how it's done.
- Okay.

1145
00:44:22,852 --> 00:44:25,355
This spot right here
is always ready for you, Soo-jin.

1146
00:44:25,588 --> 00:44:27,524
I'll take this chair out.

1147
00:44:27,891 --> 00:44:29,526
Here's the one-kick.

1148
00:44:29,592 --> 00:44:31,094
There's nothing much to it.

1149
00:44:31,161 --> 00:44:32,395
This is it.

1150
00:44:34,264 --> 00:44:35,465
Hey, you're good.

1151
00:44:35,532 --> 00:44:37,467
For two-kick, you've got to do this.

1152
00:44:38,034 --> 00:44:39,335
I'm not great with two-kicks.

1153
00:44:39,736 --> 00:44:40,870
Here's the Thomas flare.

1154
00:44:42,205 --> 00:44:43,973
THAT'S AN ADVANCED SKILL!

1155
00:44:45,241 --> 00:44:46,476
What's going on?

1156
00:44:46,543 --> 00:44:48,311
- She's the real deal.
- Hey, you're pretty good.

1157
00:44:48,378 --> 00:44:49,712
Hey, Da-hee.

1158
00:44:49,779 --> 00:44:51,114
Why don't you learn from her?

1159
00:44:51,948 --> 00:44:53,149
I'm not that good.

1160
00:44:53,216 --> 00:44:55,852
- Hey, you have a talent.
- It's just that when I was young

1161
00:44:55,919 --> 00:44:57,754
I badly wanted to become a singer.

1162
00:44:57,820 --> 00:44:59,689
That was my dream, you see.

1163
00:44:59,756 --> 00:45:01,858
What songs did you dance to
back in the day?

1164
00:45:02,091 --> 00:45:03,326
Shinhwa's music, of course.

1165
00:45:03,393 --> 00:45:05,228
- So you grew up with Shinhwa.
<i>- Troubleshooter?</i>

1166
00:45:05,295 --> 00:45:06,996
<i>Let's Go </i>or <i>T.O.P?</i>

1167
00:45:07,263 --> 00:45:08,331
<i>Troubleshooter?</i>

1168
00:45:08,398 --> 00:45:10,733
<i>TROUBLESHOOTER</i>
IS THE BEST SONG OF SHINHWA!

1169
00:45:10,800 --> 00:45:12,101
I danced to many of H.O.T's songs.

1170
00:45:12,168 --> 00:45:13,303
- Like what?
- My goodness.

1171
00:45:13,369 --> 00:45:14,837
<i>- Warrior's Descendants </i>is intense.
<i>- Candy</i>.

1172
00:45:14,904 --> 00:45:15,905
<i>Candy?</i>

1173
00:45:15,972 --> 00:45:18,841
When I was in elementary school,
we danced to <i>We Are The Future.</i>

1174
00:45:19,676 --> 00:45:21,277
- Did you dance as well?
- Well...

1175
00:45:21,344 --> 00:45:22,946
Are you a dancer, too?

1176
00:45:23,146 --> 00:45:24,247
Oh, well...

1177
00:45:24,314 --> 00:45:26,316
I know the moves
to <i>We Are The Future.</i>

1178
00:45:26,382 --> 00:45:27,884
At first, you stand like this.

1179
00:45:29,085 --> 00:45:30,086
Oh, wow.

1180
00:45:30,153 --> 00:45:31,221
CHANNELING 12-YEAR-OLD DANIEL

1181
00:45:31,521 --> 00:45:33,923
A TRIP DOWN THE MEMORY LANE

1182
00:45:33,990 --> 00:45:35,858
HERE ARE HYUK'S ENDEAVORS

1183
00:45:40,530 --> 00:45:43,399
DANCE MACHINE

1184
00:45:43,466 --> 00:45:46,169
RIGHT UP THE ALLEY FOR FANS OF H.O.T.

1185
00:45:46,703 --> 00:45:49,105
IN THE ZONE

1186
00:45:50,273 --> 00:45:51,541
There's a move like that.

1187
00:45:52,442 --> 00:45:53,443
BOUNCE

1188
00:45:53,509 --> 00:45:54,978
OLD AGE BRINGING HIM DOWN...

1189
00:45:55,044 --> 00:45:56,312
He's got it, all right.

1190
00:45:56,379 --> 00:45:57,680
That's true, but...

1191
00:45:58,081 --> 00:46:00,016
BUT HIS OLD AGE...

1192
00:46:00,283 --> 00:46:02,118
You get the idea, right?

1193
00:46:02,185 --> 00:46:04,020
- Of course!
- You got it, right?

1194
00:46:04,554 --> 00:46:07,090
ENCORE PERFORMANCE OUT OF JOY

1195
00:46:07,457 --> 00:46:09,292
- The whole team held this pose.
- Hey, you're good.

1196
00:46:09,359 --> 00:46:10,560
- You have a talent, dude.
- Yeah.

1197
00:46:10,860 --> 00:46:11,894
He's a good dancer.

1198
00:46:12,161 --> 00:46:13,696
That's the opening move.

1199
00:46:13,763 --> 00:46:14,964
- Really?
- Sure.

1200
00:46:16,165 --> 00:46:20,036
THERE'S NO COOLING DOWN
HIS BURNING PASSION

1201
00:46:20,103 --> 00:46:23,172
EVERYONE SINGING TOGETHER

1202
00:46:23,539 --> 00:46:24,841
Oh, man.

1203
00:46:24,907 --> 00:46:25,975
You're pretty good.

1204
00:46:26,042 --> 00:46:27,610
- You can say that again.
- You've got a talent.

1205
00:46:27,677 --> 00:46:28,911
- I have?
- Sure.

1206
00:46:29,178 --> 00:46:30,346
No one can deny that.

1207
00:46:30,413 --> 00:46:31,881
I MISS THE GOOD OLD DAYS

1208
00:46:32,482 --> 00:46:34,250
- He's surprisingly good.
- Yeah.

1209
00:46:34,317 --> 00:46:35,652
Actually

1210
00:46:35,718 --> 00:46:36,719
I have a serious concern.

1211
00:46:36,786 --> 00:46:37,920
- What's up?
- It's because...

1212
00:46:37,987 --> 00:46:39,255
- What's this about?
- It's because...

1213
00:46:39,322 --> 00:46:40,757
DID I DO SOMETHING WRONG AGAIN?

1214
00:46:40,823 --> 00:46:43,393
AM I GETTING AN EARFUL AGAIN?

1215
00:46:43,893 --> 00:46:47,230
I checked out a blind date
for Daniel.

1216
00:46:48,064 --> 00:46:49,465
- The group date?
- Yeah.

1217
00:46:50,099 --> 00:46:51,434
- What?
- What's this?

1218
00:46:52,101 --> 00:46:55,338
ON DAY ONE,
DANIEL SHARED HIS HOUSE SQUAD GOALS

1219
00:46:55,538 --> 00:46:56,839
One is a group date

1220
00:46:56,906 --> 00:46:59,075
where people use their personal items
to select their partners.

1221
