01:04:03,532 --> 01:04:04,933
Sure. Which color do you want?

1704
01:04:05,000 --> 01:04:06,001
This is how it goes, right?

1705
01:04:06,068 --> 01:04:07,302
- Exactly.
- Aim higher.

1706
01:04:07,369 --> 01:04:08,470
There you go.

1707
01:04:08,537 --> 01:04:09,604
Don't blink.

1708
01:04:10,639 --> 01:04:11,640
- There you go.
- It's there.

1709
01:04:11,707 --> 01:04:13,075
- Good job.
- You're all set.

1710
01:04:13,408 --> 01:04:15,243
- You're going for an odd-eyed look?
- Yeah.

1711
01:04:16,144 --> 01:04:17,145
GRAY, BROWN

1712
01:04:17,212 --> 01:04:19,414
WAY TOO BOLD!
AN ODD-EYED LOOK, NO LESS

1713
01:04:19,481 --> 01:04:21,550
- Should we all follow suit?
- Yes, I'd like that.

1714
01:04:21,616 --> 01:04:22,918
- Really?
- Yeah, I dig it.

1715
01:04:22,984 --> 01:04:24,086
AN ODD-EYED GIRL GROUP

1716
01:04:25,554 --> 01:04:27,522
- Do-yeon.
- Yeah?

1717
01:04:27,589 --> 01:04:29,658
Do you have towels
you'd like to wash?

1718
01:04:29,958 --> 01:04:31,593
- I'm going to wash them now.
- Towels?

1719
01:04:31,660 --> 01:04:33,362
HOUSEKEEPING SERVICE
FOR THE LADIES GOING OUT

1720
01:04:33,428 --> 01:04:34,429
Thanks.

1721
01:04:34,496 --> 01:04:35,831
I'll have them washed

1722
01:04:35,897 --> 01:04:37,399
- Thanks.
- during your dance lesson.

1723
01:04:37,466 --> 01:04:38,934
- Okay.
- Hang on.

1724
01:04:39,000 --> 01:04:41,103
Who's your tutor anyway?

1725
01:04:41,169 --> 01:04:42,170
What's with the makeup?

1726
01:04:42,237 --> 01:04:44,039
I've never seen
either of you look like this.

1727
01:04:44,673 --> 01:04:46,007
Think of it as our armor.

1728
01:04:46,074 --> 01:04:47,142
Is it armor?

1729
01:04:47,209 --> 01:04:48,410
You want to look tough?

1730
01:04:48,477 --> 01:04:50,278
Do-yeon is even wearing
a belly shirt.

1731
01:04:50,746 --> 01:04:52,748
No one calls it
a belly shirt anymore.

1732
01:04:52,814 --> 01:04:54,116
- What's it called, then?
- Crop top.

1733
01:04:54,182 --> 01:04:55,183
Crop top, of course.

1734
01:04:55,250 --> 01:04:56,351
- Crop top?
- Sure.

1735
01:04:56,418 --> 01:04:58,887
It's my first time seeing Do-yeon
wearing contacts.

1736
01:04:59,421 --> 01:05:00,655
- Guess he noticed.
- He caught that.

1737
01:05:00,722 --> 01:05:01,923
PERCEPTIVE TO HER SLIGHT CHANGES

1738
01:05:02,157 --> 01:05:04,559
Take a close look at our contacts.

1739
01:05:04,626 --> 01:05:06,495
I wondered why your eyes
all looked bluish.

1740
01:05:06,561 --> 01:05:08,530
- You got them in different shades?
- Yes, I'm odd-eyed now.

1741
01:05:08,597 --> 01:05:11,066
- We all chose different colors.
- You all went for that look?

1742
01:05:11,133 --> 01:05:12,467
- Are we leaving now?
- Yes, let's go.

1743
01:05:12,534 --> 01:05:14,669
- We should get going.
- You look so glamorous.

1744
01:05:14,736 --> 01:05:16,705
- What do you think?
- I like it. You look cool.

1745
01:05:17,639 --> 01:05:19,708
We'll amaze the world with our dance.
Or someone, at least.

1746
01:05:19,775 --> 01:05:21,276
You guys do seem
like you're all talk.

1747
01:05:21,843 --> 01:05:24,012
All talk?

1748
01:05:24,646 --> 01:05:26,314
- We'll go to get our dance craze.
- Got it.

1749
01:05:26,381 --> 01:05:27,783
"Dance craze"?

1750
01:05:28,250 --> 01:05:29,518
Let's go get our dance craze.

1751
01:05:30,886 --> 01:05:32,421
- Here we go.
- Let's go.

1752
01:05:33,388 --> 01:05:35,056
Let's go own it.

1753
01:05:38,126 --> 01:05:40,495
<i>Charismatic hip-hop.</i>

1754
01:05:40,562 --> 01:05:42,764
<i>I should be dancing</i>
<i>at Bulgwang station.</i>

1755
01:05:42,831 --> 01:05:44,900
<i>When it comes to dance,</i>
<i>all it takes is confidence.</i>

1756
01:05:44,966 --> 01:05:46,701
You look cool from the back, Soo-jin.

1757
01:05:46,768 --> 01:05:48,003
Let's go crush it.

1758
01:05:49,671 --> 01:05:53,408
WE ARE A LADIES GROUP

1759
01:05:53,809 --> 01:05:56,077
CHUCKLING

1760
01:05:56,978 --> 01:05:58,246
Let's go.

1761
01:05:58,313 --> 01:05:59,681
I'll drive.

1762
01:05:59,748 --> 01:06:01,216
GAINING NEW EXPERIENCES
THANKS TO HOUSEMATES

1763
01:06:02,250 --> 01:06:04,519
Team Odd Eyes, let's go.

1764
01:06:04,586 --> 01:06:05,587
All right.

1765
01:06:05,954 --> 01:06:08,056
We observe this world
with different perspectives.

1766
01:06:08,123 --> 01:06:10,459
That's why we're called "Odd Eyes."
What do you say?

1767
01:06:10,525 --> 01:06:12,527
Are you a genius of what?

1768
01:06:12,594 --> 01:06:14,095
You're brilliant.

1769
01:06:14,162 --> 01:06:15,363
You're so kind.

1770
01:06:15,864 --> 01:06:17,399
We see the world
with different perspectives?

1771
01:06:17,466 --> 01:06:19,568
MEANWHILE,
THE MAIN DANCER IS PUTTING ON MAKEUP

1772
01:06:19,634 --> 01:06:21,903
FOCUSED

1773
01:06:24,573 --> 01:06:25,774
FLICKS A GLANCE

1774
01:06:27,809 --> 01:06:29,411
She skipped her makeup to do mine.

1775
01:06:29,478 --> 01:06:33,014
Don't worry about it, Do-yeon.
I'm making progress just fine.

1776
01:06:33,081 --> 01:06:34,282
In the car, though?

1777
01:06:34,349 --> 01:06:35,417
COMMON SCENE IN WOMEN'S CARS

1778
01:06:35,617 --> 01:06:37,018
I'll try to drive smoothly.

1779
01:06:37,085 --> 01:06:38,153
I WON'T SLAM ON THE BRAKES

1780
01:06:38,220 --> 01:06:41,957
Our tutors are undeniably amazing.

1781
01:06:42,491 --> 01:06:44,759
- Let's do our best, okay?
- Sure.

1782
01:06:44,960 --> 01:06:46,761
To be honest, my heart is racing.

1783
01:06:47,429 --> 01:06:50,065
The two dancers you reached out to
have always been my favorite.

1784
01:06:50,999 --> 01:06:53,568
When you called Ms. Monika
by her nickname so casually earlier

1785
01:06:53,635 --> 01:06:55,170
my heart skipped a beat.

1786
01:06:55,237 --> 01:06:56,838
I can't thank you enough.

1787
01:06:56,905 --> 01:06:58,440
It's making my heart flutter.

1788
01:06:59,641 --> 01:07:01,710
It's an invaluable opportunity
for us, certainly.

1789
01:07:01,776 --> 01:07:02,777
You bet it is.

1790
01:07:02,844 --> 01:07:04,446
When else could we learn
from those great people?

1791
01:07:04,513 --> 01:07:05,847
ALL EXCITED
ABOUT DA-HEE'S HOUSE SQUAD GOAL

1792
01:07:05,914 --> 01:07:07,415
<i>- Thank you.</i>
<i>- Welcome.</i>

1793
01:07:07,482 --> 01:07:10,118
ARRIVED AT THE DANCE STUDIO
WITH BEATING HEARTS!

1794
01:07:14,856 --> 01:07:15,924
What's the matter?

1795
01:07:15,991 --> 01:07:18,593
DO-YEON'S FRIENDS AND DANCE TUTORS
ARE VISIBLE THROUGH THE CRACK

1796
01:07:18,660 --> 01:07:21,463
MONIKA
LEADER OF THE DANCE CREW PROWDMON

1797
01:07:21,530 --> 01:07:24,432
LIP J
NATION'S LEADING WAACKING DANCER

1798
01:07:24,499 --> 01:07:26,868
PRACTICING THE DANCE
THEY'RE GOING TO TEACH THEM TODAY

1799
01:07:28,737 --> 01:07:29,738
What's the matter?

1800
01:07:30,739 --> 01:07:32,240
- What's wrong?
- Are they right there?

1801
01:07:32,307 --> 01:07:33,675
- They're dancing.
- Behind the door?

1802
01:07:33,742 --> 01:07:34,843
- Just behind the door?
- Really?

1803
01:07:35,544 --> 01:07:36,978
MANAGED TO CRACK THE DOOR OPEN

1804
01:07:37,045 --> 01:07:39,981
BUT COULDN'T DARE ENTER THE STUDIO

1805
01:07:40,048 --> 01:07:41,316
NOTICES DA-HEE

1806
01:07:41,383 --> 01:07:42,817
RUSHING OVER TO GREET THEM

1807
01:07:42,884 --> 01:07:44,085
Why just stand there, Do-yeon?

1808
01:07:44,452 --> 01:07:45,453
Come right in!

1809
01:07:45,720 --> 01:07:47,255
- Do-yeon!
- Hello.

1810
01:07:47,322 --> 01:07:49,291
- Hello.
- Hello.

1811
01:07:49,357 --> 01:07:50,458
You're so beautiful.

1812
01:07:51,393 --> 01:07:52,827
Look, she's in sweats!

1813
01:07:53,562 --> 01:07:55,630
- I've never seen you like this.
- Gosh, you're wearing contacts.

1814
01:07:55,697 --> 01:07:57,332
REMEMBERS TO SHOW OFF THE CONTACTS

1815
01:07:57,399 --> 01:07:58,500
ABASHED

1816
01:07:58,567 --> 01:07:59,834
- Love your red sweats.
- Hello.

1817
01:07:59,901 --> 01:08:01,670
Hey, I have this T-shirt!

1818
01:08:01,736 --> 01:08:02,837
- I have it at home.
- Really?

1819
01:08:02,904 --> 01:08:04,005
You're giving dancer vibes for sure.

1820
01:08:04,072 --> 01:08:05,840
- I've put some effort...
- One hundred percent.

1821
01:08:06,374 --> 01:08:07,709
You came fully prepared for it.

1822
01:08:07,776 --> 01:08:08,843
Gosh, Do-yeon.

1823
01:08:09,511 --> 01:08:11,580
Since I'm the bridge
between these two teams

1824
01:08:11,646 --> 01:08:13,548
- I'll give you all a briefing.
- You're the bridge.

1825
01:08:13,615 --> 01:08:14,849
Actually, I asked for your help

1826
01:08:14,916 --> 01:08:17,485
because one
of Da-hee's House Squad Goals is

1827
01:08:17,552 --> 01:08:19,955
to master the dance to <i>like JENNIE</i>

1828
01:08:20,155 --> 01:08:21,356
and shoot a video.

1829
01:08:21,423 --> 01:08:23,792
So that was Da-hee's goal.

1830
01:08:23,858 --> 01:08:25,560
For us tutors

1831
01:08:25,627 --> 01:08:27,295
we have to try something
called a level test.

1832
01:08:28,997 --> 01:08:31,733
We have to determine
how advanced we can go.

1833
01:08:33,034 --> 01:08:36,304
- Showcase all your skill sets here.
- All of it.

1834
01:08:36,605 --> 01:08:37,872
- Show them one-kick and two-kick.
- I can do it.

1835
01:08:37,939 --> 01:08:39,374
- Show them.
- Let's see what you got.

1836
01:08:40,008 --> 01:08:41,242
What about the Thomas flare?

1837
01:08:41,309 --> 01:08:43,011
- Yes, try that.
- Show them the Thomas flare...

1838
01:08:43,078 --> 01:08:44,346
Thomas flare?

1839
01:08:44,412 --> 01:08:45,513
Really?

1840
01:08:45,580 --> 01:08:47,148
THAT GOT HER HOPES UP

1841
01:08:47,682 --> 01:08:49,551
Yes, I can do Thomas flare.
I'll sit on the floor

1842
01:08:50,785 --> 01:08:52,954
and spin around like this.
This is it, right?

1843
01:08:53,021 --> 01:08:55,123
HIP-HOP DANCER WANNABE
SHOWS OFF HER SKILLS

1844
01:08:55,557 --> 01:08:57,459
THAT'S MY FRIEND

1845
01:08:57,525 --> 01:08:59,728
First off, that was impressive.

1846
01:08:59,794 --> 01:09:00,929
How should I say this...

1847
01:09:00,996 --> 01:09:03,198
You'd do a wonderful job
cleaning the floor, too.

1848
01:09:04,666 --> 01:09:05,834
- Of course.
- And also...

1849
01:09:05,900 --> 01:09:07,636
I can sweep the whole studio
if you'd like.

1850
01:09:08,603 --> 01:09:10,772
- Show us what you've got, Do-yeon.
- You must have something.

1851
01:09:10,839 --> 01:09:12,040
ME?

1852
01:09:15,210 --> 01:09:16,845
THIS IS AN OLDIE TRYING TO AMUSE YOU

1853
01:09:16,911 --> 01:09:18,413
HER TUTORS BURST INTO LAUGHTER

1854
01:09:18,480 --> 01:09:20,582
HER FRIENDS TRY THEIR BEST
NOT TO LAUGH TOO HARD

1855
01:09:20,649 --> 01:09:23,451
- You picked this up from somewhere.
- You've watched some clips.

1856
01:09:23,518 --> 01:09:25,286
- Of course, I did.
- Something like this...

1857
01:09:25,353 --> 01:09:27,188
I actually watched the clip
of you dancing.

1858
01:09:27,255 --> 01:09:28,590
That's where it came from.

1859
01:09:28,657 --> 01:09:31,259
- And something like this.
- You checked that out, too?

1860
01:09:31,326 --> 01:09:33,194
You didn't use the same-side arm
and leg together, right?

1861
01:09:33,261 --> 01:09:34,696
ONE PERSON FAILS TO LAUGH
WITH THE OTHERS

1862
01:09:34,763 --> 01:09:36,264
I'm sure you practiced a lot, Da-hee.

1863
01:09:36,331 --> 01:09:38,667
You must be prepared for this.

1864
01:09:38,733 --> 01:09:40,235
I'm not prepared at all.

1865
01:09:40,301 --> 01:09:41,770
That's why I came to learn, you see.

1866
01:09:41,836 --> 01:09:43,004
I must say...

1867
01:09:43,071 --> 01:09:44,072
PRESSURE IS GETTING TO HER

1868
01:09:44,139 --> 01:09:46,741
The way you're wearing that cap
gives off the vibe of a dancer

1869
01:09:46,808 --> 01:09:48,176
with ten years under her belt.

1870
01:09:48,243 --> 01:09:50,578
- She's blending in perfectly, too.
- In styling, yes.

1871
01:09:50,645 --> 01:09:52,747
Yeah, Da-hee. Go for it.

1872
01:09:53,682 --> 01:09:54,849
TUTORS TURN ON A RANDOM SONG

1873
01:09:54,916 --> 01:09:55,917
- Oh, great.
- Love it.

1874
01:09:57,052 --> 01:09:59,054
NERVOUS

1875
01:09:59,120 --> 01:10:00,655
FEELING SHY

1876
01:10:00,722 --> 01:10:01,790
You've got this.

1877
01:10:01,856 --> 01:10:04,059
VIBING

1878
01:10:04,859 --> 01:10:05,894
Oh, my.

1879
01:10:05,960 --> 01:10:08,129
EMBARRASSMENT DOESN'T STOP HER
FROM SHOWING HER SKILLS

1880
01:10:08,196 --> 01:10:10,331
- That's her instinct kicking in.
- She's the best.

1881
01:10:10,899 --> 01:10:12,333
- Best by far!
- Look at her go.

1882
01:10:12,400 --> 01:10:13,501
- Amazing!
- What do I do?

1883
01:10:13,568 --> 01:10:14,936
You're the best!

1884
01:10:15,003 --> 01:10:16,237
- Amazing!
- What do I do?

1885
01:10:16,805 --> 01:10:18,139
HERE GOES NOTHING

1886
01:10:18,840 --> 01:10:21,476
AS EXPECTED FROM OUR MAIN DANCER!

1887
01:10:21,543 --> 01:10:23,078
She's definitely the best.

1888
01:10:23,812 --> 01:10:25,380
DOMINATING THE FLOOR

1889
01:10:25,447 --> 01:10:27,515
- All right!
- Oh, no.

1890
01:10:28,383 --> 01:10:29,451
Let's stop this, guys.

1891
01:10:29,884 --> 01:10:30,985
BUT HER BODY'S STILL MOVING

1892
01:10:31,052 --> 01:10:32,120
See? That's her instinct.

1893
01:10:32,187 --> 01:10:34,255
Great.

1894
01:10:34,322 --> 01:10:36,558
You have a passion for dancing.

1895
01:10:36,624 --> 01:10:39,894
Your body reacted
to the tune instinctively.

1896
01:10:39,961 --> 01:10:43,198
We can now see who's an A-student
and who's a C-student.

1897
01:10:43,565 --> 01:10:45,500
It seems there's a gap
between the members' skills.

1898
01:10:45,567 --> 01:10:47,268
WHO GOT AN A AND WHO GOT A C?

1899
01:10:47,335 --> 01:10:48,603
Already?

1900
01:10:48,670 --> 01:10:49,671
There's no helping it.

1901
01:10:49,738 --> 01:10:51,005
JUST SMILING

1902
01:10:52,006 --> 01:10:54,809
We've learned
the choreography of <i>like JENNIE.</i>

1903
01:10:54,876 --> 01:10:56,177
Our crew didn't work on it

1904
01:10:56,244 --> 01:10:58,279
but we did our homework
for this class.

1905
01:10:58,346 --> 01:10:59,514
We studied it.

1906
01:11:00,749 --> 01:11:03,451
We wanted to give you a good lesson.

1907
01:11:04,285 --> 01:11:07,222
A MEGA HIT OF 2025
JENNIE'S <i>LIKE JENNIE</i>

1908
01:11:08,289 --> 01:11:12,527
THE POWERFUL DANCE TEMPTED SO MANY
TO CREATE DANCE CHALLENGE VIDEOS

1909
01:11:12,594 --> 01:11:14,195
<i>I admired the charismatic vibe</i>

1910
01:11:14,262 --> 01:11:17,766
<i>and felt like dancing,</i>
<i>exuding that same energy myself.</i>

1911
01:11:17,832 --> 01:11:19,801
ON THE OTHER HAND,
HER FRIENDS ARE CONCERNED

1912
01:11:19,868 --> 01:11:20,869
What do we do?

1913
01:11:21,803 --> 01:11:23,304
You can do it.

1914
01:11:23,605 --> 01:11:25,106
Shall we try dancing to the music?

1915
01:11:25,874 --> 01:11:27,609
Just get the feel of the song.

1916
01:11:28,076 --> 01:11:29,077
PASSION IGNITED

1917
01:11:29,144 --> 01:11:30,145
Ready.

1918
01:11:34,916 --> 01:11:36,417
Pull your arms up.

1919
01:11:36,484 --> 01:11:37,552
BRIGHT EYED

1920
01:11:37,619 --> 01:11:39,420
THE MOST ANIMATED SHE'S BEEN
EVER SINCE MOVING IN

1921
01:11:39,487 --> 01:11:41,689
Hands up. Left foot.
Hands up. Right foot.

1922
01:11:41,890 --> 01:11:42,991
Can I add head flicks like this?

1923
01:11:43,057 --> 01:11:44,926
COULDN'T HELP
BUT ADD A LITTLE PERSONAL TWIST

1924
01:11:44,993 --> 01:11:45,994
Sure, you can.

1925
01:11:46,060 --> 01:11:47,095
But not now.

1926
01:11:48,463 --> 01:11:50,932
- Who told you to act cool?
- Sorry.

1927
01:11:50,999 --> 01:11:53,468
- Who gave you the go-ahead?
- I just did it on reflex.

1928
01:11:53,535 --> 01:11:56,004
I felt like flexing a bit. I'm sorry.

1929
01:11:56,070 --> 01:11:57,539
In our field,
we call it adding a flavor.

1930
01:11:57,605 --> 01:11:58,606
Adding a flavor?

1931
01:11:58,673 --> 01:12:00,141
- But...
- She's going at it.

1932
01:12:00,208 --> 01:12:02,243
- That's because...
- I really felt like doing this.

1933
01:12:02,310 --> 01:12:05,079
Is it possible to skip the basics
and go straight to the flavor part?

1934
01:12:05,146 --> 01:12:06,214
That's possible.

1935
01:12:06,281 --> 01:12:08,516
But you have to promise us
not to tell anyone we taught you.

1936
01:12:09,317 --> 01:12:11,219
I promise not to try
to add my own flavor.

1937
01:12:11,286 --> 01:12:13,955
I'LL ADD FLAVOR LATER ON

1938
01:12:14,022 --> 01:12:16,524
After this,
we get a series of danceable moves.

1939
01:12:16,724 --> 01:12:19,427
We'll open our knees

1940
01:12:19,494 --> 01:12:20,562
and swing our arms this way.

1941
01:12:20,628 --> 01:12:23,865
Like the chorus
from Kim Hyun-jung's song?

1942
01:12:24,499 --> 01:12:26,134
A CALLBACK TO A 25-YEAR-OLD SONG

1943
01:12:26,201 --> 01:12:28,036
RECOGNIZED THE REFERENCE

1944
01:12:28,102 --> 01:12:30,872
We need to tell them that the knees
must move in the opposite direction.

1945
01:12:30,939 --> 01:12:32,974
- If they move together like this...
- Someone did that?

1946
01:12:33,041 --> 01:12:34,742
That'd be Kim Jeong-ryeol's bit.

1947
01:12:34,809 --> 01:12:35,977
It's his signature move.

1948
01:12:36,044 --> 01:12:37,378
My knees move in the same direction.

1949
01:12:38,746 --> 01:12:39,948
Who moved their knees together?

1950
01:12:40,014 --> 01:12:41,015
ME, MA'AM

1951
01:12:41,082 --> 01:12:42,650
<i>I couldn't get my body</i>
<i>to follow the moves.</i>

1952
01:12:43,117 --> 01:12:45,987
SQUEAK, SQUEAK

1953
01:12:47,222 --> 01:12:48,756
HER HIPS WON'T FOLLOW HER DIRECTIONS

1954
01:12:48,823 --> 01:12:49,891
How do I do that?

1955
01:12:50,758 --> 01:12:53,194
INCURABLE CONDITION

1956
01:12:54,062 --> 01:12:56,798
I CAME TO SUPPORT MY HOUSEMATE

1957
01:12:56,865 --> 01:12:57,932
Just how...

1958
01:12:57,999 --> 01:12:59,534
AND MY CONFIDENCE IS TANKING

1959
01:13:01,936 --> 01:13:04,138
I SLAYED THE OLD DANCES...

1960
01:13:04,205 --> 01:13:05,273
THE NEW ONES DON'T VIBE WITH ME

1961
01:13:05,340 --> 01:13:06,341
In the plié squat position...

1962
01:13:06,641 --> 01:13:08,042
- Shall we, then?
- Sure.

1963
01:13:08,910 --> 01:13:09,911
Here we go.

1964
01:13:10,912 --> 01:13:11,913
Ready.

1965
01:13:13,948 --> 01:13:14,983
LIKE DA-HEE

1966
01:13:15,049 --> 01:13:16,251
Push, push.

1967
01:13:16,618 --> 01:13:18,186
FOCUSED

1968
01:13:19,954 --> 01:13:20,955
Two.

1969
01:13:21,022 --> 01:13:22,290
Great.

1970
01:13:24,425 --> 01:13:25,627
ALMOST ADDED HER FLAVOR...

1971
01:13:25,693 --> 01:13:26,961
SUCKS IN AIR

1972
01:13:27,028 --> 01:13:29,330
THAT STOPPED THE URGE

1973
01:13:29,397 --> 01:13:30,932
Get your backpacks on. Now, kick.

1974
01:13:31,266 --> 01:13:32,834
To the back. Let's have fun.

1975
01:13:33,134 --> 01:13:34,869
To the side. Jump rope.

1976
01:13:34,936 --> 01:13:37,171
HER ENERGY LEVEL GOES UP
AS THE SONG REACHES ITS CLIMAX

1977
01:13:39,407 --> 01:13:41,075
WE'RE GETTING A DÉJÀ VU

1978
01:13:41,142 --> 01:13:43,311
THE FAMILIAR MOVE HAS EXCITED HER

1979
01:13:43,378 --> 01:13:45,880
- Did you originate this dance?
- That move?

1980
01:13:45,947 --> 01:13:47,949
Well, I wouldn't call it a dance.

1981
01:13:49,017 --> 01:13:50,351
It's more of a slapstick for laughs.

1982
01:13:50,418 --> 01:13:51,653
BETWEEN A DANCE AND A SLAPSTICK

1983
01:13:53,221 --> 01:13:56,124
I felt embarrassed about that part,
so I changed it to this.

1984
01:13:56,190 --> 01:13:57,492
I'll stick to my bit.

1985
01:13:58,226 --> 01:14:00,061
CRACKING UP

1986
01:14:00,361 --> 01:14:01,696
It's sticking with me just fine.

1987
01:14:02,563 --> 01:14:04,165
I see the marks on my skin
whenever I shower.

1988
01:14:04,232 --> 01:14:05,300
That's enough.

1989
01:14:05,366 --> 01:14:06,401
Honestly...

1990
01:14:06,467 --> 01:14:07,969
WHAT GOT YOU SO EXCITED, DO-YEON?

1991
01:14:08,369 --> 01:14:10,805
THIS INTROVERT
WHO ONLY READS THE NEWSPAPER

1992
01:14:10,872 --> 01:14:12,740
HAS BECOME A NEW PERSON

1993
01:14:13,174 --> 01:14:15,677
SHE TAGGED ALONG
AND FOUND HER ALTER EGO

1994
01:14:15,743 --> 01:14:16,744
All right.

1995
01:14:16,811 --> 01:14:18,513
Let's move on to Da-hee's favorite.

1996
01:14:18,579 --> 01:14:19,580
The hand gestures.

1997
01:14:19,647 --> 01:14:21,215
Form an L and bring it to the center.

1998
01:14:21,516 --> 01:14:23,318
I LOVE ADDING PERSONAL TOUCHES

1999
01:14:23,384 --> 01:14:24,485
FOCUSED

2000
01:14:24,552 --> 01:14:27,255
Then move to the right

2001
01:14:27,355 --> 01:14:31,526
and pop your chest four times.

2002
01:14:31,926 --> 01:14:33,761
This is a real challenge
that will strain your abs.

2003
01:14:34,028 --> 01:14:35,630
And then... You nailed it, Soo-jin.

2004
01:14:35,964 --> 01:14:37,765
Isolation is her thing.

2005
01:14:37,832 --> 01:14:38,833
Isolation?

2006
01:14:38,900 --> 01:14:41,035
WITNESS MY DANCE SKILL

2007
01:14:41,803 --> 01:14:44,305
I FINALLY GOT TO THE PART
WHERE MY TALENT CAN SHINE

2008
01:14:44,706 --> 01:14:47,075
EVEN MONIKA IS SURPRISED

2009
01:14:47,875 --> 01:14:49,844
AN ENCORE PERFORMANCE
AFTER REGAINING HER CONFIDENCE

2010
01:14:49,911 --> 01:14:51,446
That reminds me of krumping.

2011
01:14:51,512 --> 01:14:52,880
- You're right.
- Absolutely.

2012
01:14:52,947 --> 01:14:54,182
You're pretty knowledgeable.

2013
01:14:54,248 --> 01:14:55,550
I love watching people dance.

2014
01:14:57,986 --> 01:15:00,788
THIS IS KRUMP DANCE
I PICKED UP BY WATCHING VIDEOS

2015
01:15:01,522 --> 01:15:04,392
MORE HYPED UP THAN DA-HEE

2016
01:15:04,459 --> 01:15:06,794
SQUEALS

2017
01:15:06,861 --> 01:15:09,464
SHOCKED BY THE VISUAL

2018
01:15:09,530 --> 01:15:10,531
It's all about confidence.

2019
01:15:10,598 --> 01:15:12,066
I actually dig it.

2020
01:15:12,533 --> 01:15:13,901
FINAL HURDLE
BEFORE RECORDING THE VIDEO

2021
01:15:13,968 --> 01:15:15,770
Then, we go,
thump, thump, thump, thump.

2022
01:15:16,537 --> 01:15:19,073
- Boom, up, up. Pop your chest.
- Boom, up, up. Pop your chest.

2023
01:15:19,140 --> 01:15:20,975
- Thump, thump, thump.
- Thump, thump, thump.

2024
01:15:21,042 --> 01:15:22,710
Da-hee's following along nicely.

2025
01:15:23,011 --> 01:15:25,913
MA'AM, I WANT A COMPLIMENT, TOO

2026
01:15:27,148 --> 01:15:29,517
RAISING HER ENERGY LEVEL IN RESPONSE

2027
01:15:30,151 --> 01:15:32,620
DO-YEON'S HIGH ENERGY IS CONTAGIOUS

2028
01:15:32,887 --> 01:15:34,255
WHOSE HOUSE SQUAD GOAL
WAS THIS AGAIN?

2029
01:15:34,756 --> 01:15:37,025
NOT SURE ABOUT THE MOVES,
BUT EVERYONE'S EXCITED

2030
01:15:38,993 --> 01:15:42,730
EXHAUSTED AFTER TRYING
TO KEEP UP WITH DO-YEON

2031
01:15:42,797 --> 01:15:44,932
People hearing the audio only
would think we're killing it.

2032
01:15:45,666 --> 01:15:48,002
Here's what we're going to do.

2033
01:15:48,236 --> 01:15:50,638
The viewers aren't likely to think,
"Hey, they're good."

2034
01:15:50,705 --> 01:15:51,973
They'd likely go, "They seem mid

2035
01:15:52,340 --> 01:15:54,942
but I guess they're good,
judging by their loud voices."

2036
01:15:55,009 --> 01:15:56,344
- We'll confuse them.
- Great.

2037
01:15:56,411 --> 01:15:58,579
- We'll blow them away by the end.
- Exactly.

2038
01:15:58,646 --> 01:15:59,647
WAIT AND SEE

2039
01:15:59,714 --> 01:16:00,848
It's all about confidence.

2040
01:16:00,915 --> 01:16:01,916
I love it.

2041
01:16:01,983 --> 01:16:04,519
AN ENERGETIC CHALLENGE VIDEO
BY THE BOLD DANCERS COMING SOON

2042
01:16:04,952 --> 01:16:09,123
WHAT'S GOING ON IN GUGI-DONG HOUSE
WITH ONLY GUYS STAYING BEHIND?

2043
01:16:09,757 --> 01:16:12,927
TWO KIDULTS ARE IN HIGH SPIRITS
AFTER A GROCERY RUN

2044
01:16:12,994 --> 01:16:16,230
<i>CAPTAIN PLANET AND THE PLANETEERS</i>
THEME SONG

2045
01:16:16,297 --> 01:16:19,434
SINGING TOGETHER

2046
01:16:19,901 --> 01:16:21,502
- We're home.
- Welcome back.

2047
01:16:21,569 --> 01:16:23,371
TWO WARRIORS IN THEIR FORTIES ARE
ON THE SAME WAVELENGTH

2048
01:16:23,438 --> 01:16:24,772
I see you bought a ton of stuff.

2049
01:16:24,839 --> 01:16:26,641
Look forward to dinner this evening.

2050
01:16:26,707 --> 01:16:27,942
What are you making?

2051
01:16:28,009 --> 01:16:29,544
Pork cutlet.
We're having a fancy meal.

2052
01:16:29,610 --> 01:16:30,611
- For real?
- Sure.

2053
01:16:30,678 --> 01:16:31,779
I love it.

2054
01:16:32,313 --> 01:16:33,314
GOOD

2055
01:16:34,315 --> 01:16:38,686
GOOD

2056
01:16:39,454 --> 01:16:41,856
- Is there a supermarket close by?
- Yeah.

2057
01:16:41,923 --> 01:16:42,990
I see.

2058
01:16:44,192 --> 01:16:45,426
Gosh, it's a beautiful day.

2059
01:16:46,761 --> 01:16:48,663
The weather is perfect.

2060
01:16:48,729 --> 01:16:51,265
JAE-HYEON HAS COME TO THE YARD
TO HANG THE LAUNDRY TO DRY

2061
01:16:52,433 --> 01:16:55,570
WARM SUNLIGHT AND WIND

2062
01:16:55,636 --> 01:16:59,574
PERFECT WEATHER
TO DRY LAUNDRY OUT IN THE OPEN

2063
01:17:00,208 --> 01:17:01,576
That's what I'm talking about.

2064
01:17:04,145 --> 01:17:08,082
HOMEMAKER AHN FEELS MORE ENERGIZED
THANKS TO THE GREAT WEATHER

2065
01:17:08,850 --> 01:17:10,251
I love the sound of the wind chime.

2066
01:17:11,752 --> 01:17:14,655
THE TINKLING SOUND OF THE WIND CHIME
AT A BUDDHIST TEMPLE NEARBY

2067
01:17:14,722 --> 01:17:18,559
RINGS OUT INTO THE WHOLE NEIGHBORHOOD
WITH THE HELP OF THE WIND

2068
01:17:19,627 --> 01:17:24,599
BUT...

2069
01:17:24,665 --> 01:17:28,469
THE SOUND GROWS LOUDER

2070
01:17:29,003 --> 01:17:33,040
AND THE WIND GROWS STRONGER

2071
01:17:36,277 --> 01:17:38,412
This is making me feel anxious.

2072
01:17:39,046 --> 01:17:42,884
THE STRONG WIND KEEPS
SHAKING THE DRYING RACK

2073
01:17:43,484 --> 01:17:45,086
The weight should keep it still.

2074
01:17:46,721 --> 01:17:50,024
HANGS A BUNCH OF TOWELS
TO WEIGH THE RACK DOWN

2075
01:17:50,525 --> 01:17:51,526
Good.

2076
01:17:51,993 --> 01:17:53,261
The wind can't fling it away now.

2077
01:17:53,327 --> 01:17:55,596
HE STEPS ON IT FOR GOOD MEASURE,
BUT HE STILL FEELS ANXIOUS

2078
01:17:56,297 --> 01:17:57,632
It's giving me jitters, though.

2079
01:18:00,368 --> 01:18:03,638
TOO CONCERNED TO WALK AWAY

2080
01:18:06,307 --> 01:18:07,542
10 MINUTES LATER

2081
01:18:07,608 --> 01:18:09,844
RETURNING WITH A CUP OF COFFEE

2082
01:18:09,911 --> 01:18:11,179
It's such a beautiful day.

2083
01:18:11,979 --> 01:18:13,281
So beautiful.

2084
01:18:14,582 --> 01:18:16,284
What? Dang it.

2085
01:18:19,220 --> 01:18:23,858
THE RACK GAVE OUT IN THE END

2086
01:18:25,126 --> 01:18:27,128
I stepped away for a bit
to get some coffee!

2087
01:18:28,829 --> 01:18:29,931
It's giving me jitters, though.

2088
01:18:29,997 --> 01:18:31,666
JAE-HYEON LEFT TO GET COFFEE

2089
01:18:32,300 --> 01:18:35,503
EXACTLY 10 SECONDS LATER

2090
01:18:36,270 --> 01:18:38,706
SHAKING OMINOUSLY

2091
01:18:41,209 --> 01:18:44,545
THE WIND'S STRONG EMBRACE
KNOCKED IT OVER

2092
01:18:45,980 --> 01:18:48,549
A TRAGEDY BROUGHT ON
BY A WHIMSICAL COFFEE BREAK

2093
01:18:49,717 --> 01:18:51,052
I kind of knew this would happen.

2094
01:18:51,118 --> 01:18:52,720
A ROUGH DAY FOR HOMEMAKER AHN

2095
01:18:54,655 --> 01:18:56,290
HANGING LIMPLY

2096
01:18:58,426 --> 01:18:59,660
SIGHS DEEPLY

2097
01:19:01,796 --> 01:19:02,797
Come along.

2098
01:19:04,198 --> 01:19:08,302
THE RECOVERED TOWELS
ENDED UP BACK IN THE WASHER

2099
01:19:08,369 --> 01:19:09,370
IN MERE 15 MINUTES

2100
01:19:09,437 --> 01:19:10,638
<i>I knew it.</i>

2101
01:19:10,938 --> 01:19:12,340
<i>Things can happen.</i>

2102
01:19:12,406 --> 01:19:14,175
WILL THE HOUSEMATES
GET THEIR TOWELS WITHIN THE DAY?

2103
01:19:14,242 --> 01:19:15,576
Time for a little workout.

2104
01:19:16,677 --> 01:19:20,047
MEANWHILE, AP IS DOWN
IN THE BASEMENT TO WORK OUT

2105
01:19:25,119 --> 01:19:29,657
CHANNELING ROCKY OUT OF THE BLUE

2106
01:19:30,291 --> 01:19:32,893
ADDED BACKGROUND MUSIC
USING THE COIN KARAOKE MACHINE

2107
01:19:34,428 --> 01:19:36,063
ADDS A BATTLE CRY

2108
01:19:36,464 --> 01:19:38,266
AP'S AT-HOME WORKOUT IS DIFFERENT

2109
01:19:38,332 --> 01:19:40,868
IT'S ANOTHER SHOW TIME

2110
01:19:42,803 --> 01:19:45,506
FIRST ROUTINE, BENCH PRESS

2111
01:19:46,107 --> 01:19:49,944
GOOD POSTURE

2112
01:19:56,317 --> 01:19:58,819
THAT'S IT?

2113
01:20:01,389 --> 01:20:06,861
NOW THAT HE'S WARMED UP,
IT'S TIME TO...

2114
01:20:06,927 --> 01:20:10,798
SING?

2115
01:20:20,041 --> 01:20:24,645
SWITCHING TO BOXING SUDDENLY

2116
01:20:24,712 --> 01:20:29,283
ACTUALLY, HE GETS HOLD
OF A TAMBOURINE

2117
01:20:29,750 --> 01:20:33,554
WHEN IS HE GOING
TO WORK OUT PROPERLY?

2118
01:20:34,121 --> 01:20:37,858
SWAYING SIDE TO SIDE

2119
01:20:39,627 --> 01:20:44,165
NOW THAT HE'S IN THE ZONE,
HE WANTS ONE MORE SONG

2120
01:20:44,231 --> 01:20:46,801
ANOTHER VERY DRAMATIC INTERLUDE

2121
01:20:48,703 --> 01:20:52,073
THIS TIME, IT'S THE THEME SONG
OF THE 1988 ***MPICS

2122
01:20:52,139 --> 01:20:54,508
LET ME SHOW YOU THE PRINCE'S ENERGY

2123
01:20:55,109 --> 01:20:58,112
THIS TIME, HE WORKS
ON FLEXING HIS BICEPS

2124
01:20:58,179 --> 01:20:59,914
GRACEFUL

2125
01:21:06,120 --> 01:21:07,121
SIGHS

2126
01:21:08,522 --> 01:21:11,192
YET AGAIN, HE'S ONLY DONE ONE SET

2127
01:21:11,258 --> 01:21:15,963
IT SEEMS HE'S ADDING A SET
IN BETWEEN HIS BREAKS

2128
01:21:17,365 --> 01:21:20,634
SUDDENLY TRYING CHEERLEADING MOVES

2129
01:21:20,701 --> 01:21:23,170
LET'S GO, KOREA

2130
01:21:24,905 --> 01:21:27,141
TAKING A PEEK

2131
01:21:28,175 --> 01:21:31,946
WHAT THE HECK IS HE DOING NOW?

2132
01:21:32,380 --> 01:21:34,882
WELCOME TO MY LOUNGE

2133
01:21:35,516 --> 01:21:37,184
You're supposed
to keep your head down.

2134
01:21:37,251 --> 01:21:39,487
- So I'm fooling around alone here
- Alone?

2135
01:21:39,553 --> 01:21:40,554
so no one would know.

2136
01:21:40,621 --> 01:21:42,189
I guess I'll have to give you that.

2137
01:21:42,523 --> 01:21:45,226
- You use this for music?
- It gets you in the mood.

2138
01:21:45,292 --> 01:21:46,994
- How clever.
- It gets you there.

2139
01:21:47,061 --> 01:21:48,729
- What are you doing?
- Just some weightlifting.

2140
01:21:48,796 --> 01:21:51,799
- We've got gear now.
- Simple stuff. I brought some over.

2141
01:21:53,234 --> 01:21:55,736
Are we sure it's safe?
What if it breaks?

2142
01:21:55,803 --> 01:21:56,904
GOING STRAIGHT TO THE MACHINE

2143
01:21:56,971 --> 01:21:58,239
Hey, this feels great.

2144
01:22:00,408 --> 01:22:03,043
I hear hanging helps a lot.

2145
01:22:03,110 --> 01:22:04,612
- Try a pull-up.
- No thanks.

2146
01:22:04,678 --> 01:22:05,880
- Go on.
- No, I'm sticking to this.

2147
01:22:05,946 --> 01:22:07,181
What's the point of hanging there?

2148
01:22:07,248 --> 01:22:08,549
I'm only going to...

2149
01:22:12,219 --> 01:22:13,721
JUST A SINGLE ATTACK

2150
01:22:13,788 --> 01:22:15,723
BUT DOUBLE STRIKES

2151
01:22:17,358 --> 01:22:18,692
That was pretty wild.

2152
01:22:18,759 --> 01:22:20,127
I barely touched you.

2153
01:22:20,728 --> 01:22:22,463
Don't do it, okay?

2154
01:22:22,530 --> 01:22:24,231
Oh, jeez. Don't.

2155
01:22:26,300 --> 01:22:28,636
This alone has good health benefits.

2156
01:22:28,702 --> 01:22:30,304
- It stretches your spine.
- It's just a stretch.

2157
01:22:30,371 --> 01:22:31,872
Yeah, and that's good for you.

2158
01:22:33,307 --> 01:22:34,408
YELPS

2159
01:22:34,475 --> 01:22:35,476
That wasn't you?

2160
01:22:35,543 --> 01:22:37,478
WHAT'S UP WITH HIM?

2161
01:22:37,545 --> 01:22:39,680
- You're making me paranoid.
- How come?

2162
01:22:39,747 --> 01:22:41,916
- I'm worried you'd tickle me again.
- All right, fine.

2163
01:22:42,583 --> 01:22:44,852
<i>I think we're on top</i>
<i>of the moves now.</i>

2164
01:22:44,919 --> 01:22:46,687
<i>Let's practice dancing for the clip.</i>

2165
01:22:48,289 --> 01:22:49,623
- Sounds good.
- So we can get used to it.

2166
01:22:49,690 --> 01:22:50,691
I love it.

2167
01:22:50,758 --> 01:22:51,759
NERVOUS AND EXCITED

2168
01:22:52,126 --> 01:22:53,627
- Do-yeon.
- Yeah?

2169
01:22:53,694 --> 01:22:54,728
What do you think?

2170
01:22:55,296 --> 01:22:57,364
Should I keep my cap on
for more impact?

2171
01:22:57,431 --> 01:22:58,632
Let me think.

2172
01:22:59,200 --> 01:23:01,235
Would it be better
to let my hair swish around more?

2173
01:23:01,302 --> 01:23:03,504
- I prefer you with the cap on.
- You do?

2174
01:23:04,071 --> 01:23:05,806
Let's keep Da-hee in the center
as much as we can.

2175
01:23:05,873 --> 01:23:07,775
- Oh, no.
- Take one step forward.

2176
01:23:08,742 --> 01:23:10,311
- Just do it, Da-hee.
- What?

2177
01:23:10,377 --> 01:23:11,612
Confidence!

2178
01:23:11,679 --> 01:23:12,913
GRINS

2179
01:23:12,980 --> 01:23:14,548
It's all about confidence.

2180
01:23:14,615 --> 01:23:16,517
You've got this, Da-hee.

2181
01:23:16,584 --> 01:23:17,918
- Step forward, please.
- Forward?

2182
01:23:17,985 --> 01:23:20,054
- I'll shoot close-ups first.
- Oh, really?

2183
01:23:20,120 --> 01:23:21,121
Stand closer to Da-hee.

2184
01:23:21,188 --> 01:23:22,189
Here we go.

2185
01:23:22,256 --> 01:23:23,457
NERVOUS

2186
01:23:23,524 --> 01:23:24,525
Ready.

2187
01:23:24,592 --> 01:23:25,726
A NEW EXPERIENCE THANKS TO DA-HEE

2188
01:23:27,695 --> 01:23:29,296
NEW GLINT IN HER EYES

2189
01:23:31,832 --> 01:23:35,336
INTRO GOES SMOOTHLY

2190
01:23:37,037 --> 01:23:38,706
DID DA-HEE JUST CRACK A SMILE?

2191
01:23:38,772 --> 01:23:40,207
CLOSING IN

2192
01:23:40,407 --> 01:23:43,844
FAZED BY THE CAMERA MOVING IN

2193
01:23:43,911 --> 01:23:45,145
SNEAKS A GLANCE

2194
01:23:45,880 --> 01:23:48,816
HER NEIGHBOR COVERS FOR HER
WITH HER HIGH ENERGY

2195
01:23:48,883 --> 01:23:52,520
LET'S USE THE BEST WEAPON
IN OUR ARSENAL

2196
01:23:52,586 --> 01:23:54,455
THEIR MOVES FALL APART

2197
01:23:54,522 --> 01:23:55,589
NOTHING CAN SALVAGE THIS NOW

2198
01:23:55,656 --> 01:23:56,657
Darn it.

2199
01:23:58,859 --> 01:23:59,860
Darn it.

2200
01:23:59,927 --> 01:24:00,928
Oh, no.

2201
01:24:00,995 --> 01:24:02,630
Can you please edit that out?

2202
01:24:03,531 --> 01:24:04,832
Oh, shoot.

2203
01:24:04,899 --> 01:24:06,200
ARE THEY GOING TO START CURSING NOW?

2204
01:24:06,567 --> 01:24:08,636
I'LL SEAL MY MOUTH

2205
01:24:08,869 --> 01:24:10,037
- It's okay.
- Okay.

2206
01:24:10,337 --> 01:24:12,072
Can't believe our video
ended like that.

2207
01:24:12,139 --> 01:24:13,774
A NICE START PAIRED
WITH A SORRY ENDING

2208
01:24:14,141 --> 01:24:16,343
MEANWHILE...

2209
01:24:16,777 --> 01:24:18,746
THIS WON'T DO

2210
01:24:18,979 --> 01:24:21,181
Why don't we shoot the video
for the challenge together?

2211
01:24:21,248 --> 01:24:23,350
Let's take one each
and wrap things up nicely.

2212
01:24:23,784 --> 01:24:25,452
Okay, this is a rare opportunity.

2213
01:24:26,020 --> 01:24:27,488
Who wants the spotlight first?

2214
01:24:28,188 --> 01:24:29,823
My sole priority is
that Da-hee looks amazing.

2215
01:24:29,890 --> 01:24:30,958
THE ORDER DOESN'T MATTER

2216
01:24:31,025 --> 01:24:32,560
- And you're killing it, Da-hee.
- Totally.

2217
01:24:32,626 --> 01:24:33,661
As long as she looks great

2218
01:24:33,727 --> 01:24:35,129
our House Squad Goal
is a major success.

2219
01:24:35,195 --> 01:24:37,331
I love your attitude just now.

2220
01:24:37,398 --> 01:24:40,267
SHE CAN'T SEEM TO RELAX
DESPITE HER FRIENDS' ENCOURAGEMENT

2221
01:24:40,334 --> 01:24:42,469
IN THAT CASE...

2222
01:24:42,536 --> 01:24:44,872
Why don't I do it in my own style?

2223
01:24:44,939 --> 01:24:45,973
DO-YEON STARTS FIRST

2224
01:24:46,307 --> 01:24:47,841
DO-YEON STEPS UP
INSTEAD OF NERVOUS DA-HEE

2225
01:24:47,908 --> 01:24:48,976
Is Do-yeon going first?

2226
01:24:49,710 --> 01:24:52,079
SAVED BY DO-YEON

2227
01:24:52,580 --> 01:24:54,682
I'll film it. The least I can do
is be the cameraperson.

2228
01:24:55,449 --> 01:24:56,784
Wait, what do I do first again?

2229
01:24:56,850 --> 01:24:57,851
A STYLIST? A CAMERAPERSON?

2230
01:24:58,252 --> 01:24:59,353
A FORMER INTROVERT

2231
01:24:59,420 --> 01:25:00,421
Let's roll.

2232
01:25:00,487 --> 01:25:04,058
SHE'S ENJOYING SOMETHING
SHE WOULD'VE NEVER EXPERIENCED ALONE

2233
01:25:05,526 --> 01:25:07,061
HER POSE IS ALREADY
ON A PROFESSIONAL'S LEVEL

2234
01:25:07,261 --> 01:25:08,262
FLINGING AWAY

2235
01:25:08,329 --> 01:25:10,030
DO-YEON'S CHALLENGE

2236
01:25:10,097 --> 01:25:13,434
THE INTROVERT ENERGY
HAS LEFT HER ALONG WITH HER CAP

2237
01:25:16,503 --> 01:25:19,406
EXTROVERT DO-YEON'S CHALLENGE
IS SAILING SMOOTHLY

2238
01:25:19,873 --> 01:25:20,941
CHUCKLING

2239
01:25:21,208 --> 01:25:22,943
CRISIS STRIKES
AS THE CAMERA CLOSES IN

2240
01:25:23,010 --> 01:25:24,845
ON THE VERGE OF LOSING IT

2241
01:25:29,016 --> 01:25:30,351
Oh, no. I made a mistake.

2242
01:25:30,417 --> 01:25:32,453
It's okay. Keep going.

2243
01:25:32,519 --> 01:25:33,520
It's that move next.

2244
01:25:34,722 --> 01:25:36,724
THAT'S MY THING

2245
01:25:37,057 --> 01:25:38,425
AMAZED

2246
01:25:39,660 --> 01:25:42,296
SHE'S NOT JUST BRINGING ENERGY
SHE'S GOING BERSERK

2247
01:25:45,232 --> 01:25:47,167
LETTING EVERYTHING GO
AND LOSING HERSELF IN THE MOMENT

2248
01:25:50,004 --> 01:25:51,839
GRACING THE END
WITH AN ENDING FAIRY POSE

2249
01:25:51,905 --> 01:25:53,073
My gosh.

2250
01:25:54,041 --> 01:25:55,042
She went on a rampage.

2251
01:25:55,109 --> 01:25:57,578
THESE DANCERS HAVE NEVER SEEN
A CHALLENGE VIDEO LIKE THIS BEFORE

2252
01:25:58,512 --> 01:26:00,180
Her cap went so far.

2253
01:26:00,247 --> 01:26:02,383
DISCARDED HER INTROVERT'S SHELL

2254
01:26:03,117 --> 01:26:06,186
FINALLY RELAXED
THANK YOU, DO-YEON

2255
01:26:06,420 --> 01:26:07,421
I feel so refreshed now.

2256
01:26:07,488 --> 01:26:08,656
REFRESHED TO HAVE HELPED DA-HEE

2257
01:26:08,722 --> 01:26:10,357
- That was great.
- I didn't expect the krumping part.

2258
01:26:10,424 --> 01:26:12,626
LOCKS IN THANKS TO DO-YEON'S ASSIST

2259
01:26:12,693 --> 01:26:13,694
I'm so tired.

2260
01:26:13,761 --> 01:26:15,562
FINALLY, IT'S TIME
TO REALIZE DA-HEE'S DREAM

2261
01:26:15,629 --> 01:26:16,630
Let's try this.

2262
01:26:17,598 --> 01:26:19,867
- Take the center stage, and we'll...
- That's for the better.

2263
01:26:20,167 --> 01:26:22,202
But that way,
I can't follow your moves.

2264
01:26:22,269 --> 01:26:23,837
We will indeed move to the back

2265
01:26:23,904 --> 01:26:25,139
but only after this part.

2266
01:26:25,205 --> 01:26:26,940
- Okay.
- That's the show we'll put on.

2267
01:26:27,541 --> 01:26:29,977
UNDER A TON OF STRESS

2268
01:26:30,844 --> 01:26:32,613
SO MANY CELEBRATED DANCERS TRIED THIS

2269
01:26:33,013 --> 01:26:34,715
DA-HEE'S DREAM

2270
01:26:34,782 --> 01:26:37,351
HAPPENS TO BE
A DIFFICULT DANCE CHALLENGE

2271
01:26:37,985 --> 01:26:40,587
HOW WILL
DA-HEE'S <i>LIKE JENNIE </i>VIDEO TURN OUT?

2272
01:26:40,654 --> 01:26:43,590
GROWING NERVOUS AS WELL

2273
01:26:45,359 --> 01:26:48,495
IT'S HOUSE SQUAD GOAL TIME
NO LAUGHTER, ALL SERIOUSNESS

2274
01:26:48,562 --> 01:26:52,866
DA-HEE'S CHALLENGE

2275
01:26:52,933 --> 01:26:55,836
A THRILLING PERFECT SYNCHRONIZATION

2276
01:26:58,906 --> 01:27:01,408
A NATURAL FORMATION SHIFT

2277
01:27:03,877 --> 01:27:06,013
DOMINATING THE CENTER OF THE STAGE

2278
01:27:06,080 --> 01:27:07,915
SERIOUS

2279
01:27:07,981 --> 01:27:09,717
YOU'RE DOING GREAT!

2280
01:27:11,785 --> 01:27:16,256
CHIC BEAUTY SHINING IN THE CENTER
WITH LIP J AND MONIKA BY HER SIDE

2281
01:27:18,058 --> 01:27:20,928
IT'S FINALLY TIME
TO SHOWCASE MY OWN FLAVOR

2282
01:27:21,428 --> 01:27:22,996
YOU GO, GIRL

2283
01:27:24,164 --> 01:27:27,568
THE CHALLENGE DRAWS CLOSE TO AN END

2284
01:27:27,634 --> 01:27:28,635
Great.

2285
01:27:29,703 --> 01:27:31,238
All right.

2286
01:27:31,538 --> 01:27:32,606
GET A LOAD OF MY OWN FLAVOR

2287
01:27:33,540 --> 01:27:35,008
A FLAVORFUL ENDING POSE

2288
01:27:36,643 --> 01:27:40,047
- That was perfect.
- Great job.

2289
01:27:40,114 --> 01:27:41,381
We've got a masterpiece now.

2290
01:27:41,448 --> 01:27:43,016
Amazing.

2291
01:27:43,417 --> 01:27:45,319
- How are you so good?
- I'm wondering the same thing.

2292
01:27:45,719 --> 01:27:47,855
THE MOMENT THE CAMERA STOPPED,
DA-HEE'S FLAVOR MODE WENT OFF

2293
01:27:48,489 --> 01:27:50,791
- You were amazing.
- I'm embarrassed.

2294
01:27:50,858 --> 01:27:52,860
<i>It was so satisfying.</i>

2295
01:27:52,926 --> 01:27:54,895
<i>I think I poured all my energy</i>
<i>into that dance.</i>

2296
01:27:54,962 --> 01:27:57,097
REWATCHING THE CHALLENGE VIDEO

2297
01:27:57,164 --> 01:27:59,199
I LOVE IT SO MUCH

2298
01:27:59,266 --> 01:28:02,202
LET'S REALIZE OUR DREAMS ONE BY ONE
BEFORE IT'S TOO LATE

2299
01:28:02,269 --> 01:28:03,637
To be honest

2300
01:28:03,704 --> 01:28:05,372
I felt like I became JENNIE.

2301
01:28:05,439 --> 01:28:07,574
Seriously, I mean it.

2302
01:28:07,808 --> 01:28:12,279
<i>Having Do-yeon and Soo-jin</i>
<i>by my side really helped me.</i>

2303
01:28:12,346 --> 01:28:13,347
TOGETHER WE FOUND THE COURAGE

2304
01:28:13,413 --> 01:28:17,284
<i>This experience made me realize</i>
<i>that I can keep taking lessons.</i>

2305
01:28:17,351 --> 01:28:18,852
<i>As long as I can enjoy it</i>

2306
01:28:18,919 --> 01:28:21,989
the training hours
will become meaningful for me.

2307
01:28:22,055 --> 01:28:23,924
I'm seriously considering it.

2308
01:28:24,691 --> 01:28:28,362
COMING SOON!
WATCH DANIEL REALIZE HIS DREAM

2309
01:28:28,428 --> 01:28:30,164
GROUP DATE IS JUST THE PRELUDE!

2310
01:28:30,230 --> 01:28:32,933
THERE ARE EXPERIENCES
YOU CAN ONLY ENJOY AS A GROUP

2311
01:28:33,000 --> 01:28:37,171
AND THEY WILL CONTINUE
ON WITH THEIR SITCOM-LIKE DAYS!

2312
01:28:37,237 --> 01:28:40,607
I checked out a blind date
for Daniel.

2313
01:28:41,241 --> 01:28:42,409
- What?
- What's this?

2314
01:28:42,476 --> 01:28:45,379
DANIEL ON HIS FIRST-EVER GROUP DATE

2315
01:28:46,413 --> 01:28:47,414
<i>Why did we hold hands?</i>

2316
01:28:47,781 --> 01:28:50,050
AT THE SECOND ROUND OF TWENTY

2317
01:28:50,117 --> 01:28:56,123
EXPERIENCING NEW
AND UNFAMILIAR BUTTERFLIES

2318
01:28:56,757 --> 01:28:57,758
<i>Let's think about this.</i>

2319
01:28:57,825 --> 01:29:00,227
Let's say we both like the same girl.

2320
01:29:00,294 --> 01:29:01,495
What are you going to do?

2321
01:29:01,562 --> 01:29:03,096
<i>- I wondered, "What's this?"</i>
- Who?

2322
01:29:03,163 --> 01:29:04,765
AP and Aurora?

2323
01:29:04,832 --> 01:29:06,400
AS THEIR HEART'S SIGNALS GET TANGLED

2324
01:29:06,466 --> 01:29:08,335
If you go again, let's go together.

2325
01:29:08,402 --> 01:29:11,738
A TENSE RIVALRY
BETWEEN TWO MEN SPARKS

2326
01:29:12,005 --> 01:29:13,740
Wait, let go. Have a seat.

2327
01:29:14,942 --> 01:29:17,144
I never back down
when it comes to love.

2328
01:29:17,211 --> 01:29:19,479
<i>I'm the same way.</i>
<i>I go all out when I love someone.</i>

2329
01:29:20,113 --> 01:29:22,182
<i>LOVE AND WAR, </i>GUGI-DONG EPISODE

2330
01:29:26,220 --> 01:29:28,222
Subtitles by Jeongwoo Kim
